#. Greek (Dante) sky culture name
msgid "Greek (Dante)"
msgstr "希腊 (但丁)"

#. Greek (Dante) sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"Dante Alighieri mentions several stars and a few constellations: predominantly, the zodiacal constellation of Gemini. The Twins occurs in his texts (in the comedia as well as his poems). As Dante is not an astronomer but a person with broad knowledge, his view of the constellations is highly like not based upon observations of the sky but on manuscripts that he read. Therefore, we chose to take the zodiacal constellation images from Michael Scotus whose manuscript was very popular in Dante's time.\n"
"\n"
"Dante Alighieri was a citizen of Florence, Italy, who was later banned and lived at several places in Northern Italy. The comedia was written around 1300 but finished only short before his death in 1321. It is commonly assumed that the story plays in around the Christian festival of Easter in 1300 CE."
msgstr ""
"但丁·阿利吉耶里（Dante Alighieri）在其作品中曾提及若干恒星及少量星座，其中尤为突出的是黄道星座双子座。这位诗人（在《神曲》及其他诗作中）多次提及这对双生子。由于但丁并非天文学家，而是一位博学之士，其星座观念极有可能并非源于实际天象观测，而是基于他所研读的手抄本。因此，我们选择采用但丁时代广为流传的迈克尔·斯科特手稿中的黄道星座图像。\n"
"\n"
"但丁·阿利吉耶里原为意大利佛罗伦萨市民，后遭流放，辗转于意大利北部多地。《神曲》创作始于约1300年，直至1321年诗人逝世前才完稿。学界普遍认为，书中故事的发生时间设定在公元1300年基督教复活节前后。"

#. Greek (Dante) sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"### How this Sky Culture was made\n"
"\n"
"The Dante experts of the German Dante Society selected some text passages with astronomical references in order to present them at Planetarium Jena in the dome. Professor Blume's suggestion that Dante likely had Michael Scotus's drawings of the constellations in mind was accepted. Therefore, we copied these drawings and mapped them onto the stars. The \"16\" bright stars that are mentioned by Dante are usually interpreted by romanists as the stars of first magnitude in the Almagest. Therefore, these stars where highlighted with the \"star\"-symbol in Stellarium. Additionally, we painted a chariot (wagon) and a horn.\n"
"\n"
"Dante calls the seven bright stars of Ursa Major \"The Chariot\", the constellation of Ursa Minor \"The Horn\", and possibly refers to Corona Borealis when he mentions a ring of stars. The latter interpretation is in our view unlikely but is discussed among researchers which is why we marked the stars of Corona Borealis as it is described in the Almagest."
msgstr ""
"### 该星空文化的构建过程\n"
"\n"
"德国但丁学会的但丁研究专家们遴选了一批蕴含天文指涉的文本段落，旨在耶拿天文馆的穹顶剧场中进行呈现。布鲁姆教授提出的\"但丁心目中可能参照了迈克尔·斯科特绘制的星座图\"这一观点被采纳。因此，我们复制了这些古老绘图并将其与实际星位进行匹配。但丁提及的\"16\"颗亮星通常被罗马语系学者解读为《天文学大成》中所载的一等星。为此，我们在Stellarium软件中为这些恒星特别标注了星形符号。此外，我们还绘制了车驾（马车）与号角意象。\n"
"\n"
"但丁将大熊座的七颗亮星称为\"车驾\"，将小熊座称作\"号角\"，而在提及恒星组成的环状结构时，可能指向北冕座。尽管后一种解读在我们看来依据不足，但学界对此存在讨论，故我们仍按《天文学大成》的记载标定了北冕座的恒星。"

