#. Indian (Nakshatras) sky culture name
msgid "Indian (Nakshatras)"
msgstr "印度 (Nakshatras)"

#. Indian (Nakshatras) sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"First historical proofs of nakṣatra are given in the Vedic culture which is archaeologically attested in the Indus Valley before 1000 BCE [#1],[#2],[#5],[#6]. It is known from traditional religious texts and rituals that astronomy was used for timekeeping in that time. When the Indus culture started to spread to the Ganges Plateau which has a different climate, flora and fauna, Vedic cultural astronomy was reworked and a new religious text of that time, the Arthavaveda (900 to 600 BCE), preserves a complete set of constellations called ‘nakṣatra’ (नक्षत्र). The first complete non-religious description, the Vedāṅgajyotiṣa, dates to roughly 300 BCE, and the standardized origin (Ashvini as first) was set in the first century BCE or CE. Hinduism took over the nakshatras. In the first centuries CE, astrological ideas from the Graeco-Babylonian world, including the zodiac as a division of the ecliptic into twelve equal sections, was added to the older Vedic nakshatra-division. Since the middle of the first millennium CE, the system is used in its present form. \n"
"\n"
"The number of stars per nakshatra-constellations may vary in different sources. In this sky culture, we present only one single historical source: the depictions in Tirupperunthurai (Athmanathaswamy temple) near Aranthangi, India, 10th century CE. There, they are drawn at two occasions in exactly the same way: engraved in a doorway of stone, and imprinted in a tiruvasi, a silver arch from the temple's main chamber."
msgstr ""
"纳沙特拉(nakṣatra)最早的历史证据可追溯至吠陀文化，考古学证实该文化于公元前1000年前已存在于印度河流域。 "
"[#1],[#2],[#5],[#6]从传统宗教文献与仪式可知，当时天文学已被用于计时。当印度河文化开始向气候、动植物群落迥异的恒河高原扩散时，吠陀天文学体系被重新整合，当时的新宗教文献《阿闼婆吠陀》（公元前900-600年）完整保存了名为\"nakṣatra\""
" "
"(नक्षत्र)的星宿体系。最早的非宗教性完整记载见于《吠陀支天文篇》，年代约为公元前300年；而标准化的星宿排序（以阿斯温尼星宿为首）确立于公元前1世纪或公元1世纪。印度教沿用了纳沙特拉体系。公元1世纪前后，来自希腊-"
"巴比伦世界的占星观念（包括将黄道划分为十二等分的黄道带系统）被融入古老的吠陀星宿划分体系。自公元5世纪中叶以来，该体系一直以现有形式沿用至今。不同文献中记载的纳沙特拉星群所包含恒星数量存在差异。在本天文文化研究中，我们仅采用单一历史文献来源：公元10世纪印度阿兰坦吉附近蒂鲁珀伦图赖（阿特马纳塔斯瓦米神庙）的星宿图像。该星宿图以两种完全相同的形态呈现：一是石刻门廊上的浮雕，二是神庙主殿银制拱门\"蒂鲁瓦西\"上的印记。"

#. Indian (Nakshatras) sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"In the second millennium BCE, the nakshatras were likely observed as rising constellations were the moon stands. The moon travels roughly 12° per day (360° in 30 days). However, historians proved that in later times, the nakshatras were observed in culmination [#4]. The moon then stands in the meridian together with some constellations. It is much easier to observe simultaneous culminations, as the air mass is much thinner there than at the horizon. Additionally, it simplifies the coordinate system and timekeeping, as simultaneously culminating asterisms share the same right ascension (hour) circle. \n"
"\n"
"### Sky\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"### Moon and Sun\n"
"\n"
"The nakshatras are defined as a circle of constellations to observe the motion of the moon. However, the Sun also travels the same path. The nakshatra of the sun is called the maLe nakshatra. \n"
"\n"
"### Planets\n"
"\n"
"The planets travel the same path but were not considered. \n"
"\n"
"### Zodiac\n"
"\n"
"The nakshatra are a lunar frame of reference, developed independent of the Babylonian zodiac but later merged with it due to exchange with the Greek culture which had adopted it already. The term \"kṣatra\" means \"brilliance and \"na\" is a negation; so \"nakṣatra\" means \"no brilliance\"/ \"not bright\". In most cases, the stars used to define the asterisms that define the lunar stations (nakṣatra) are faint - with the exceptions of Spica, Betelgeuse, Arcturus. The fact that they are not bright and, thus, not easily visible, might have triggered the development of a coordinate system (which is, by definition, invisible), as the mental step from almost-invisible to invisible-by-definition is small. It is unknown when this step of mathematisation happened in the Vedic culture, but its existance in the first millennium BCE is highly likely while the zodiac schema (Rāśi, राशिः) was only adopted in India in the first millennium CE. \n"
"\n"
"### Milky Way\n"
"\n"
"The Milky Way is not incorporated in this set."
msgstr ""
"在公元前第二个千年，人们可能通过观测月亮所在位置的升起的星群来识别纳沙特拉。月亮每日运行约12度（30天运行360度）。然而，历史学家证明，在后期阶段，纳沙特拉的观测方式转变为观测其**中天**现象【参考文献#4】。此时月亮与某些星群同时位于子午线上。观测同时中天的星群更为简便，因为该方向的大气厚度远小于地平线附近。此外，这简化了坐标系与计时系统，因为同时中天的星群共享相同的赤经圈（时圈）。\n"
"\n"
"### 星空\n"
"\n"
"### 月亮与太阳\n"
"\n"
"纳沙特拉被定义为一圈用于观测月亮运行的星群。然而，太阳也遵循相同的路径运行。太阳所在的纳沙特拉被称为**male nakshatra**。\n"
"\n"
"### 行星行星虽沿相同路径运行，但未被纳入该体系考量。\n"
"\n"
"### 黄道带纳沙特拉是一种以月球为参照的坐标体系，其发展独立于巴比伦黄道带，后因与已吸收黄道带的希腊文化交流而与之融合。\"kṣatra\"意为\"光辉\"，\"na\"为否定前缀；故\"nakṣatra\"可解为\"无光\"/\"不亮\"。除角宿一、参宿四、大角星等例外，用于界定这些月球站点（纳沙特拉）的星群大多较为暗淡——它们不够明亮、不易观测的特性，可能推动了坐标系统（其本质是不可见的）的发展，因为从\"几乎不可见\"到\"定义上不可见\"的思想跨越并不遥远。目前尚不确定这一数学化进程在吠陀文化中发生于何时，但很可能在公元前第一个千年内已存在；而黄道带体系（Rāśi，राशिः）直到公元第一个千年才在印度被采纳。\n"
"\n"
"### 银河\n"
"\n"
"银河未被纳入该星宿体系。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Ashvini
msgid ""
"The meaning is \"Horse Head\", is the first nakshatra since the canonisation"
" in the first millennium CE."
msgstr "其意为“马头”，是自公元第一个千年内体系规范化后被确立的首个纳沙特拉（星宿）。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Bharani
msgid "The meaning is \"Bearer\"."
msgstr "其意为“持载者”。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Krittika
msgid ""
"The meaning of the name is uncertain, but it's a name for the Pleiades, "
"mythologically represented by seven damsels."
msgstr "此名含义未明，但它指昴星团，在神话中常以七位少女的形象呈现。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Rohini
msgid ""
"Literally, the meaning is \"The Red One\", a name for reddish Aldebaran and "
"the Hyades."
msgstr "其字面意为“红色者”，指代呈红色的毕宿五及毕星团。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Mrigashira
msgid ""
"The term's literal meaning is \"Deer's Head\". It is an asterism of three "
"faint stars that seem to form a nebulous patch."
msgstr "字面意为“鹿头”，指由三颗暗淡星辰组成的星宿，其形态似一片朦胧光斑。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Ardra
msgid ""
"The sixth nakshatra has the name \"Wetness\". It is identified with "
"Betelgeuse as a single star-asterism."
msgstr "第六个纳沙特拉（星宿）名为“湿润”。它被认定为单星星宿，对应着参宿四。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Punarvasu
msgid "The term means \"Twin-Restorer\" and refers to a deity."
msgstr "这个词的意思是“双重恢复者”，指的是一个神。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Pushya
msgid ""
"Pushya means \"Nourisher\" and is a name for the open star cluster M44 which"
" is surrounded by four stars forming a box-like quadrilateral."
msgstr "此星宿名意为“滋养者”，指疏散星团M44，其外围由四颗恒星构成箱状四边形结构。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Ashlesha
msgid "Ashlesha means \"Embrace\"."
msgstr "意思是“拥抱”"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Magha
msgid ""
"This name sometimes refers to the single star-asterism Regulus and sometimes"
" to a group of four stars in a zigzag pattern. The literal translation means"
" \"Bountiful\"."
msgstr "该名称有时指代单星星宿轩辕十四，有时则指代呈锯齿状排列的四星群组。其字面含义为“丰饶”。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Purva Phalguni
msgid ""
"Likely, there used to be a constellation \"Phalguni\", the Reddish, in very "
"old times that was later split into two sections to obtain a number of 27 "
"units in the path of the moon; Purva Phalguni is the \"First Reddish\"."
msgstr ""
"在远古时期，可能曾存在一个名为“Phalguni”（意为“微红者”）的星宿，后为凑足月亮轨道上的27个单元而被拆分为两部分；Purva "
"Phalguni即指“第一微红者”。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Uttara Phalguni
msgid ""
"Uttara Phalguni is the \"Second Reddish\", the second half of the Phalguni-"
"asterism, in the direction of monthly lunar motion."
msgstr "Uttara Phalguni意为“第二微红者”，指Phalguni星群的后半部分，位于月亮每月运行方向的后段。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Hasta
msgid "Hasta means \"Hand\" and refers to a group of five stars."
msgstr "Hasta意为“手”，指由五颗星组成的星群。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Chitra
msgid ""
"Chitra, the \"Bright One\", used to be a star name for most of historical "
"sources. However, in this specific engraving in the temple, interestingly, "
"this single star-asterism is drawn as two stars and not only as one as it "
"used to be the tradition. The companion is called \"Apamvatsa\" in later "
"star catalogues and also bears this name in the IAU-Catalogue of Star Names."
msgstr ""
"Chitra意为“光明者”，在大多数历史文献中曾作为单颗星名使用。然而，在这处神庙的特定雕刻中，这个本应沿用传统表现为单星的形象，却被绘制为两颗星。其伴星在后世星表中被称为\"Apamvatsa\"，该名称亦收录于国际天文学联合会*恒星名称目录*。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Svati
msgid "Svati is the name of a goddess."
msgstr "Svati是一位女神的名字。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Vishakha
msgid ""
"The literal meaning is \"Forked\"; it is the name of an asterims in Libra, "
"but only the identification of alpha and beta Librae is certain."
msgstr "其字面含义为“分叉的”，是天秤座中一个星群的名称，但仅能确定其包含天秤座α星与β星。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Jyeshtha
msgid "The name means \"Eldest\" but it is unknown what it signifies."
msgstr "该名称意为“最年长者”，但其具体指代尚不明确。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Mula
msgid ""
"Mula, the \"Root\", is located in the area of Sco which contains some of the"
" brightest clouds of the Milky Way with a significant dark stripe in the "
"middle, and also many bright stars. Hence, it is uncertain if the name "
"refers to a group of (up to ten) stars or to a pattern of bright or dark "
"clouds."
msgstr ""
"Mula意为“根”,位于天蝎座区域，该此处包含银河系中一些最明亮的星云，中央还有一条显著的暗带，同时分布着许多亮星。因此，尚不确定其名称究竟是指一组（最多可达十颗）恒星，还是指明亮或暗色星云所构成的某种图案。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Purva Ashadha
msgid ""
"Ashadha, the Invincible, was the name of a larger constellation that was "
"split into two parts, the first of which is the \"First Invincible\"."
msgstr "Purva Ashadha意为\"第一无敌者\"，本为一个更大的星宿，后为凑足月亮轨道上的27个单元而被拆分为两部分，此即其中\"第一\"部分。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Uttara Ashadha
msgid ""
"The \"Second Invincible\" is the second half of the formerly larger "
"constellation of Ashadha, the Invincible, in the direction of the monthly "
"motion of the moon."
msgstr "Uttara Ashadha意为\"第二无敌者\"，是原先较大的\"Ashadha\"（意为“无敌者”）星宿的后半部分，位于月亮每月运行方向的后段。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Shravana
msgid "Shravana means \"Listening\"."
msgstr "Shravana意为\"听闻\"。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Dhanishta
msgid ""
"Dhanishta, the \"Most Famous\", is the name of an easily recognisable "
"pattern of stars; it appears as a group even to inexperienced observers."
msgstr "Dhanishta意为\"最负盛名者\"，是一个易于辨认的星群名称；即便对缺乏经验的观测者而言，其星群形态也清晰可辨。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Shatabhisha
msgid ""
"Literally, the term Shatabhisha means \"Hundred Physicians\" and some "
"historical depictions really display 100 stars. Here, it is just represented"
" as a group of many."
msgstr "Shatabhisha字面意为\"百医\"，历史上确有描绘展现百颗恒星。此处仅以群星形式呈现。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Purva Bhadrapada
msgid "From the Blessed Feet, here we see the \"First Blessed Feet\"."
msgstr ""

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Uttara Bhadrapada
msgid ""
"As the Moon on its monthly path moves from west to east, the eastern part of"
" the constellation of the Blessed Feet is called \"Second Blessed Feet\"."
msgstr "由于月亮在其月度路径上自西向东运行，\"福足\"星群的东部被称为\"第二福足\"。"

#. Description of Indian (Nakshatras) constellation Revati
msgid ""
"Revati means the \"Prosperous\". In the canonical counting the last "
"nakshatra, harbinger of the new cycle."
msgstr "\"Revati\"意为\"丰饶者\"。在规范排序中，它是最后一个纳沙特拉（星宿），象征新周期的开端。"

