#. Modern sky culture introduction section in markdown format
#. Modern (IAU) sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The modern sky culture is used internationally by modern astronomers, and is"
" the official scheme of The International Astronomical Union. It has "
"historical roots in Ancient Greek astronomy, with influences from Islamic "
"astronomy."
msgstr "现代天文学家在国际上使用现代星空文化，这是国际天文学联合会的官方计划。它源于古希腊天文学，并受到伊斯兰天文学的影响。"

#. Modern sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The modern sky culture divides the celestial sphere into 88 areas of various sizes called constellations, each with precise boundary, issued by the International Astronomical Union in 1922. These constellations have become the standard way to describe the sky, replacing similar sets in other sky cultures exhaustively in daily usage.\n"
"\n"
"The constellations in use today are based mainly on ancient Greek constellations depicted by Ptolemy in his book the Almagest during the 2nd century CE. In the subsequent centuries, this book has been translated from Greek into Arabic (6th to 9th century) and later to medieval Latin. In the Arabic more than in the Latin tradition, the Ptolemaic figures were enriched and transformed by native Arabic constellations and star names.\n"
"\n"
"In the 16-18th centuries, European astronomers suggested new constellations to fill the gaps between northern constellations (e.g. the constellation of \"the lynx\" for an area close to the Great Bear but with stars so faint that you would need the eyes of a lynx to see them) and also created new constellations in the southern part of the sky which had not been visible to Ptolemy. These new constellations were usually named after new technical inventions of the early modern period (e.g. a chemical furnace, a balloon, an air pump) or exotic animals (e.g. a chamaeleon, a tucan, a paradise bird). Among them several constellations were also named with political consideration to honor certain kings or patrons.\n"
"\n"
"In the beginning of the 20th century, the IAU (International Astronomical Union) aimed for a large clean-up: in 1922, it officially accepted the list of 88 constellation names. In 1928 it also defined precise constellation boundaries [#40] still in use today.\n"
"\n"
"### Extras\n"
"\n"
"In the 2nd century CE, Ptolemy in Alexandria published a multi-volume book which summarised the astronomical knowledge of the time, rooted in a tradition of mathematical astronomy since Hipparchus (at least 265 years earlier). In the subsequent centuries, this book has been translated from Greek into Arabic (6th to 9th century), from Arabic into Latin, and later, from the original ancient Greek into medieval Latin. Due to this transformation, it is now known under the artificial name Almagest, derived from the Arabic title [#46].\n"
"\n"
"The Almagest star catalogue (books VII and VIII) has been depicted many times in the Islamic as well as in the Christian astronomical traditions. Often, the figures were re-drawn in order to adapt them to the taste of art of the epoch. In the Arabic more than in the Latin tradition, the Ptolemaic figures were enriched and transformed by native Arabic constellations and star names. Therefore, this sky culture displays a modern descendant of the Ptolemaic one with traces of translations, misunderstandings, transformations, and deliberate additions.\n"
"\n"
"In 1603 the lawyer and hobby astronomer Johann Bayer from Augsburg, Germany, made a new celestial atlas, called Uranometria [#41]. In this atlas, he introduced a systematic naming of stars starting with alpha, the brightest, beta, the second brightest, gamma, the third ... within a constellation. Subsequently, it was established to name a star with a Greek letter and the Latin constellation name in casus genitive.\n"
"\n"
"In the 18th century, the century of great atlases (Flamsteed, Fortin, Bode: [#42][#43]), new constellations were added to fill the gaps between northern constellations. Additionally, there were suggestions to create new constellations in the southern part of the sky which had not been visible to Ptolemy. European astronomers visited the European colonies and instead of asking the native people for their constellations, the Europeans were creative. This way, many new technical inventions of the early modern period were depicted in constellations (e.g. a chemical furnace, a balloon, an air pump) as well as exotic animals (e.g. a chamaeleon, a tucan, a paradise bird).\n"
"\n"
"The problem was that sometimes astronomers did not agree with each other and, thus, atlases showed deviations from each other.\n"
"\n"
"After many centuries of astronomers taking liberties in interpretation of the Ptolemaic original, there were many variants of constellations. As constellations are a positioning system, i.e. astronomers describe positions in the sky relative to stars and stars relative to constellations (like \"Betelgeuse\", Orion's right shoulder), it is necessary to use constellation names and star names uniformly all over the world.\n"
"\n"
"In the \"Fin de siècle\", there were upcoming suggestions in the astronomical community to unify the system of constellations and star names [#44].\n"
"\n"
"The IAU, only founded in 1919, in 1928 defined the boundaries of these areas [#43] and not the way of drawing artwork or connecting lines within them. Consequently several sub-cultures of painting figures and drawing simplified stickfigures were developed during the 20th and 21st century. We provide some of them as further sky cultures.\n"
"\n"
"### Constellations\n"
"\n"
"These constellations are based mainly on the Ptolemaic tradition which had been used in all three Abrahamitic religions and, thus, was common in the Near East, in Europe and its colonies on all continents. However, between the ancient Greek constellations there were gaps of areas with only faint stars belonging to no constellation.[#47] In the Modern Epoch, several astronomers suggested constellation figures for these gaps, among them several political constellations to the honor of certain kings or patrons. In the late 19th century, the astronomical research community aimed for a huge clean-up to avoid ambiguities in assigning stars to constellations.\n"
"\n"
"In 1922, the IAU officially approved the list of 88 constellation names and their official abbreviations with three letters. The only remaining political constellation is Scutum, the shield of a Polish king but without mentioning the political reference anymore. The Belgian priest E. Delporte got the task to define constellation boundaries according to coordinates. In 1928, he finished the work, based on an atlas from Argentina [#51], and the IAU accepted his delimitations [#40].\n"
"\n"
"These \"constellations\" are naked areas in the sky without any stick figures or depictions [#44]. The borders simply follow the lines of right ascension and declination from the epoch 1875.0. Precession causes a slowly increasing deviation from the originally rectilinear grid. These constellations became the standard way to describe the sky, replacing similar sets in other sky cultures exhaustively in daily usage.\n"
"\n"
"Stellarium by default displays the precise RA-DEC-boundaries and a set of artwork constellations on the basis of Ptolemaic figures but following our contemporary taste of art.\n"
"\n"
"### Asterisms\n"
"\n"
"The term \"asterism\" (assembly of stars) can sometimes be used synonymously to \"constellation\". In the modern use it describes a figure which is not part of the official canon. Sometimes an asterism is a part of a constellation, e.g. the Big Dipper as part of Ursa Major, or Great Square as part of Pegasus. Other asterisms span over several constellations, e.g. the Summer Triangle or Winter Hexagon. Yet others are only visible in binoculars or telescopes and are aptly named \"telescopic asterism\", e.g. the Coathanger. They are often discussed in the observing columns of popular astronomy magazines.\n"
"\n"
"### Ray Helpers\n"
"\n"
"Seasoned observers can find their way around the sky easily. One mnemonic tool are associative chains of stars that span large distances. We show them as \"ray helpers\". These are not standardized.\n"
"\n"
"### Proper names of stars\n"
"\n"
"Ptolemy's star catalogue had the layout of a table listing the description of the star's position in the constellation's figure, the ecliptical coordinates, and the magnitude e.g.: \"The star at the tip of the tail of Ursa Minor\", \"Gem 0 1/6, +66\", \"Mag 3\".\n"
"\n"
"In most cases, the star names evolved by astronomer's systematical abbreviations of these descriptions, e.g., a first astronomer abbreviated in a text \"tip of the tail\", a next astronomer drew a map with less space and wrote only \"tail\" next to the star and this name remained. Over centuries, these descriptions were translated into Arabic and Latin, and in some cases the translators or scribes made mistakes because of misreading or misspelling of the Arabic words (e.g. the Arabic \"yad al gauza\", the hand of the giant woman, was mangled to the common term \"Betelgeuse\").\n"
"\n"
"However, there are also a few original Greek words like the red star \"Antares\", the counterpart of Ares (Mars), and even a few original Babylonian terms like \"Shargaz\", the Sting, in Scorpius. Our modern, most recent IAU star names [#45] are a renewed mixture, also with influences or even politically wanted additions of star names from the non-Ptolemaic sky cultures, e.g. the traditional Pingsing, a Chinese star name for a star in Hydra (its meaning is only \"star\", a reminescence to his lonely position), or newly adopted star names from Polynesian, Hawaiian, or Aboriginal cultures for names of stars with exoplanets.\n"
"\n"
"The IAU is the only scientifically accepted authority to assign new names to stars. Commercial exploits like \"star name registries\", who sell stars for commemorative purposes or as gifts, only sell printed pieces of paper. These names are not approved and never used by scientists."
msgstr ""
"现代天空文化将天球划分为88个不同大小的区域，称为星座，每个区域都有精确的边界，由国际天文学联合会于1922年发布。这些星座已成为描述天空的标准方式，在日常使用中彻底取代了其他天空文化中的类似星座。\n"
"\n"
"今天使用的星座主要基于托勒密在公元2世纪的《天文学大成》（Almagest）一书中描绘的古希腊星座。在随后的几个世纪里，这本书从希腊语被翻译成阿拉伯语（6世纪至9世纪），后来又被翻译成中世纪的拉丁语。在阿拉伯语中，托勒密数字比在拉丁语传统中更丰富，并被阿拉伯本土的星座和恒星名称所丰富和改造。\n"
"\n"
"在16-18世纪，欧洲天文学家提出了新的星座来填补北方星座之间的空白（例如，靠近大熊的地区的“猞猁”星座，但恒星非常微弱，你需要猞猁的眼睛才能看到它们），并在托勒密看不到的天空南部创造了新的星座。这些新的星座通常以现代早期的新技术发明（如化学炉、气球、气泵）或外来动物（如变色龙、蜥蜴、天堂鸟）命名。其中几个星座也是出于政治考虑而命名的，以纪念某些国王或赞助人。\n"
"\n"
"20世纪初，国际天文学联合会（IAU）计划进行大规模清理：1922年，它正式接受了88个星座名称的名单。1928年，它还定义了至今仍在使用的精确星座边界[#40]。\n"
"\n"
"### 其他\n"
"\n"
"公元2世纪，亚历山大的托勒密出版了一本多卷本的书，总结了当时的天文学知识，这本书植根于自希帕丘斯（至少265年前）以来的数学天文学传统。在随后的几个世纪里，这本书从希腊语翻译成阿拉伯语（6世纪至9世纪），从阿拉伯语翻译成拉丁语，后来从原始古希腊语翻译为中世纪拉丁语。由于这种转变，它现在被称为Almagest，也就是《天文学大成》，源自阿拉伯语标题[#46]。\n"
"\n"
"《天文学大成》星表（第七册和第八册）在伊斯兰和基督教天文传统中多次被描绘。通常，这些人物会被重新绘制，以适应那个时代的艺术品味。在阿拉伯语中，托勒密数字比在拉丁语传统中更丰富，并被阿拉伯本土的星座和恒星名称所丰富和改造。因此，这种天空文化展现了托勒密文化的现代后裔，带有翻译、误解、转换和故意添加的痕迹。\n"
"\n"
"1603年，来自德国奥格斯堡的律师兼业余天文学家Johann Bayer制作了一本名为Uranometria的新天体图集。在这本图集中，他介绍了恒星的系统命名，从最亮的阿尔法、最亮的贝塔、第二亮的伽马、第三亮的伽马开始。。。在一个星座内。随后，它被确立为用希腊字母命名一颗恒星，用拉丁语的星座名称命名。\n"
"\n"
"在18世纪，伟大的星图集世纪（Flamsteed，Fortin，Bode:[#42][#43]），新的星座被添加以填补北方星座之间的空白。此外，有人建议在托勒密看不到的天空南部创建新的星座。欧洲天文学家访问了欧洲殖民地，欧洲人没有向当地人询问他们的星座，而是富有创造力。通过这种方式，现代早期的许多新技术发明被描绘成星座（如化学炉、气球、气泵）以及异国情调的动物（如蝘蜓、杜鹃、天堂鸟）。\n"
"\n"
"问题是，有时天文学家之间意见不一致，因此，星图集显示出彼此的不同。\n"
"\n"
"经过几个世纪的天文学家对托勒密原始星座的自由解释，星座有了许多变体。由于星座是一个定位系统，即天文学家描述了天空中相对于恒星的位置和恒星相对于星座的位置（如猎户座的右肩“参宿四”），因此有必要在世界各地统一使用星座名称和恒星名称。\n"
"\n"
"在“世纪末”，天文学界即将提出统一星座和恒星名称系统的建议[#44]。\n"
"\n"
"过几天文联合会（IAU）成立于1919年，1928年定义了这些区域的边界[#43]，而不是在其中绘制艺术品或连接线条的方式。因此，在20世纪和21世纪，几个亚文化的绘画人物和绘画简化的棍棒人物得到了发展。我们提供其中一些作为进一步的天空文化。\n"
"\n"
"### 星座\n"
"\n"
"这些星座主要基于托勒密传统，该传统在所有三种亚伯拉罕宗教中都有使用，因此在近东、欧洲及其各大洲的殖民地都很常见。然而，在古希腊星座之间有一些空白区域，有一些不属于任何星座的暗淡恒星。[#47]在现代，一些天文学家提出了一些星座填补这些空隙，其中包括几个政治星座，以纪念某些国王或赞助人。19世纪末，天文学研究界旨在进行大规模的清理，以避免在将恒星分配给星座时出现歧义。\n"
"\n"
"1922年，国际天文学联合会正式批准了88个星座名称及其三个字母的官方缩写。唯一剩下的政治星座是盾牌座，波兰国王的盾牌，但不再提及政治参考。比利时牧师E.Delporte接到了根据坐标定义星座边界的任务。1928年，他根据阿根廷的星图集完成了这项工作[#51]，国际天文学联合会接受了他的划界[#40]。\n"
"\n"
"这些“星座”是天空中没有任何人物或描绘的裸露区域[#44]。边界简单地遵循1875.0时代的赤经和赤纬线。进动导致与原始直线网格的偏差缓慢增加。这些星座成为描述天空的标准方式，在日常使用中彻底取代了其他星空文化中的类似集合。\n"
"\n"
"Stellarium默认显示精确的赤经赤纬边界和一组基于托勒密数字的艺术品星座，但遵循我们当代的艺术品味。\n"
"\n"
"### 星群\n"
"\n"
"“星群”（恒星的集合）一词有时可以与“星座”同义。在现代用法中，它描述了一个不属于官方的“恒星集合”。有时星群是星座的一部分，例如大熊座的北斗七星，飞马座的大正方形。有些星群跨越几个星座，例如夏季三角星座或冬季六边形星座。然而，有些星群仅在双筒望远镜或望远镜中可见，并被恰当地命名为“望远镜星群”，例如衣架星群。它们经常在流行天文学杂志的观测专栏中讨论。\n"
"\n"
"### 导航辅助线\n"
"\n"
"经验丰富的观测者可以很容易地在天空中找到方向。一种助记工具是跨越很远距离的恒星的联想链。我们把它们称为“导航辅助线”。这些都不是标准化的。\n"
"\n"
"### 恒星的专名\n"
"\n"
"托勒密的星表有以表格的形式，列出了恒星在星座图中的位置、黄道坐标和星等的描述，例如：\"The star at the tip of the tail of Ursa Minor\"，\"Gem 0 1/6, +66\", \"Mag 3\"。\n"
"\n"
"在大多数情况下，恒星的名字是由天文学家对这些描述的系统缩写演变而来的，例如，第一个天文学家在文本中缩写为“尾巴的尖端”，下一个天文学家在地图上画了一个更小的空间，只在恒星旁边写了“尾巴”，这个名字就保留了下来。几个世纪以来，这些描述被翻译成阿拉伯语和拉丁语，在某些情况下，翻译者或抄写员会因为误读或拼写错误而犯错误（例如，阿拉伯语中的“yad al gauza”，即女巨人的手，被曲解成常见的术语“Betelgeuse”）。\n"
"\n"
"然而，也有一些原始的希腊单词，如红星“Antares”，与Ares（火星）相对应，甚至还有一些原始的巴比伦术语，如天蝎座中的“Shargaz”、“Sting”。我们现代、最新的国际天文学联合会恒星名称[#45]是一种新的混合体，也受到非托勒密天空文化的影响，甚至是政治上想要添加的恒星名称，例如传统的平星，长蛇座中用中文名称命名的一颗恒星（它的意思只是“恒星”，让人想起他孤独的位置），或者新采用来自波利尼西亚、夏威夷或土著文化的恒星名称作为系外行星的恒星名称。\n"
"\n"
"国际天文学联合会是唯一被科学认可的为恒星命名的权威机构。像“恒星名字登记”这样的商业行为，他们出售恒星作为纪念或礼物，只出售印刷的纸张。这些名称未经批准，也从未被科学家使用过。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Andromeda
msgid ""
"Princess Andromeda, daughter of Queen Cassiopeia and King Kepheus, was chained to a rock on the coast of Ethiopia to prepare her as sacrifice to Cetus, the Sea Monster. She was rescued by Perseus.  \n"
"\n"
"In this constellation you find the nearest large galaxy, the Great Andromeda Galaxy. It is barely visible with the unaided eye in a dark rural sky."
msgstr ""
"_仙女座_即安德洛墨达公主是卡西俄佩亚王后与刻甫斯国王之女，曾被锁链束缚在埃塞俄比亚海岸的岩石上，作为献给海怪刻托的祭品。她最终被英雄珀尔修斯解救。\n"
"\n"
"在这片星座中，你可以找到离我们最近的大型星系——仙女座大星系。在乡野无光的环境下，它仅凭肉眼勉强可见。仙女座大星系的伴星系M32和M110只能用望远镜观测。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Cassiopeia
msgid ""
"Shown as the Seated Queen, Cassiopeia had boasted about her beauty, so much "
"as to enrage Poseidon. The latter sent the sea monster Cetus which ravaged "
"the coast of Ethiopia. An oracle promised Cetus would only go away when "
"Princess Andromeda would be sacrificed to Cetus."
msgstr ""
"_仙后座_即卡西奥佩娅被描绘为“端坐的王后”，她曾因过度夸耀自己的美貌而激怒了海神波塞冬。盛怒之下，波塞冬派海怪刻托肆虐埃塞俄比亚海岸。神谕宣称，除非将安德洛墨达公主献祭给海怪，否则灾难不会停止。\n"
"\n"
"仙后座的两个梅西耶天体，M52和M103，都是疏散星团。M52附近的气泡星云非常独特，心脏星云和灵魂星云是两个相邻的发射星云，"

#. Description of Modern constellation Cepheus
msgid ""
"King Kepheus of Ethiopia was husband of Cassiopeia and father of Andromeda. "
"After his wife had enraged Poseidon, he had to order that his daughter, "
"Princess Andromeda, should be sacrificed to Cetus, the sea monster."
msgstr ""
"_仙王座_是埃塞俄比亚国王克甫斯。他既是卡西奥佩娅的丈夫，也是安德洛墨达的父亲。在其妻触怒波塞冬后，他被迫下令将女儿安德洛墨达公主献祭给海怪刻托。\n"
"\n"
"仙王座的*造父一*是测定星系距离的标准烛光造父变星的原型。仙王座没有梅西叶天体，但有许多其他深空天体，包括业余天文学家喜爱的鸢尾花星云，洞穴星云，烟花星系。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Whale
msgid ""
"The Sea Monster, also called Whale, was sent by Poseidon to punish Ethiopia "
"for the heresy of Cassiopeia. It was finally killed by Perseus."
msgstr ""
"_鲸鱼座_即由波塞冬派遣的海怪，旨在惩罚卡西俄佩亚亵渎神灵而祸及的埃塞俄比亚。它最终被珀尔修斯斩杀。\n"
"\n"
"鲸鱼座有很多星系，最明亮的是棒旋星系M77。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Pegasus
msgid ""
"The Winged Horse carried Perseus on his way to rescue Princess Andromeda "
"from being sacrificed to Cetus."
msgstr ""
"_飞马座_即飞马佩加索斯。飞马驮载着珀尔修斯奔赴救援，要将安德洛墨达公主从献祭给海怪刻托的命运中解救出来。\n"
"\n"
"飞马座中有球状星团M15和一些对望远镜观测者来说有趣的星系。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Little Horse
msgid ""
"_Equuleus_, the Little Horse, is actually only a horse head and represents "
"the foal Celeris, offspring or brother of the larger horse, Pegasus. It is "
"seen next to the head of Pegasus."
msgstr ""
"_小马座_虽名为马，实则仅显现马首之形。其形象源自神驹克勒里斯——或为飞马珀伽索斯之子嗣，或为其胞弟。这尊天马之首像，始终矗立于飞马座头颅的旁侧。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Perseus
msgid ""
"The hero Perseus came in flying on Pegasus to rescue Andromeda from being "
"sacrificed. In his hand he carries Medusa's head with the variable star "
"Algol, which he presented to the sea monster Cetus just as it was about to "
"devour Andromeda. Its magic caused Cetus to immediately turn to a rock. "
"Before freeing Andromeda from her chains, he dropped the sack with Medusa's "
"head to the beach. When the surf opened the sack, nearby algae were "
"petrified into corals."
msgstr ""
"_英仙座_，即英雄珀尔修斯乘飞马佩加索斯凌空而至，在安德洛墨达即将被献祭时挺身相救。他手中高举嵌有变星大陵五的美杜莎头颅，正当海怪刻托张口欲吞噬公主之际，将其对准怪物。头颅的魔力瞬间使刻托化为岩石。在解开安德洛墨达锁链前，他将装有美杜莎头颅的布袋抛至海滩。海浪冲开布袋时，近海的水藻竟被石化成珊瑚。\n"
"英仙座星云和疏散星团众多，著名的有疏散星团M34，M76小哑铃星云。*大陵五*是大陵五型变星的原型星。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Orion
msgid ""
"The famous hunter Orion was killed by a Scorpion, but was transferred into one of the most prominent constellations, notably just opposite of Scorpius. He is accompanied by the Greater and Lesser Dogs.  \n"
"\n"
"Orion is host of one of the most spectacular star-forming regions, the Great Orion Nebula, Messier 42."
msgstr ""
"著名猎人俄里翁被蝎子刺死，后升为最耀眼的星座之一_猎户座_，恰与天蝎座遥遥相对。大犬座与小犬座始终相伴左右。\n"
"\n"
"明亮的红超巨星*参宿四*是他的右肩，蓝超巨星*参宿七*则是他的的左脚踝\n"
"\n"
"猎户座中孕育着最壮观的恒星形成区之一——猎户座大星云，即 Messier 42。另一著名的星云就是位于参宿一附近的马头星云。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Greater Dog
msgid ""
"The Greater Dog is one of Orion's hunting companions. Its main star, "
"*Sirius*, is the brightest of the fixed stars."
msgstr ""
"_大犬座_是俄里翁的忠实战友。其主星*天狼星*，是夜空中最明亮的恒星。\n"
"\n"
"大犬座中疏散星团众多。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lesser Dog
msgid "The Lesser Dog is one of Orion's hunting companions."
msgstr "_小犬座_是俄里翁的狩猎伙伴之一。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Hare
msgid "_Lepus_, the hare, is hiding just below the hunter Orion."
msgstr ""
"_天兔座_就藏在猎户座的下方，有时被表示为被猎人和他的猎犬追赶的野兔\n"
"天兔座有一个梅西叶天体，球状星团 M79。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Charioteer
msgid ""
"_Auriga_, the charioteer, was born with crippled legs. He invented the wheel and built his wagon to overcome his handicap. Its main star, *Capella*, represents a goat which accompanies him. \n"
"\n"
"In this constellation you can find a nice selection of open star clusters."
msgstr ""
"_御夫座_，这位驭车的天神，生来腿部残疾。为克服身障，他发明了车轮并亲手打造了战车。其主星*五车二*象征伴随他身旁的山羊。\n"
"\n"
"在这片星座中，你能欣赏到一系列精美的疏散星团。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Great Bear
msgid ""
"_Ursa Major_, the Great Bear, represents Callisto. Once a beautiful nymph, she was seduced by Zeus. His wife Hera was enraged and converted her into a bear. Zeus could not change that, but he could raise her to the stars. But again, Hera interfered so that the Bear could not take a bath in the Okeanos. This means, from ancient Greece the constellation was circumpolar, always above the horizon. Meanwhile, precession allows the Bear to at least submerge her feet in the sea. The seven brightest stars are called the Plough or Big Dipper in English but have other names in other cultures. \n"
"\n"
"Ursa Major contains a few nice galaxies for small telescopes."
msgstr ""
"_大熊座_象征卡利斯托。她曾经是一个美丽的仙女，被宙斯引诱。宙斯之妻赫拉震怒之下将其化为熊身。宙斯虽无法逆转咒语，却将她升上星空成为星座。然而赫拉再度干涉，令大熊永远无法沉入俄刻阿诺斯之海沐浴——这意味着在古希腊时期，此星座始终围绕天极运行，永不离地平线。如今因岁差之故，大熊至少已能将双足浸入海中。其最亮的七颗星在英语中称为“犁”，“大斗”，在中国被称为“北斗”，在不同文化中有不同的名字。\n"
"\n"
"大熊座中包含数个适合小型望远镜观测的美丽星系。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lesser Bear
msgid ""
"_Ursa Minor_, the Lesser Bear may be Arkas, son of Callisto, who is commemorated as Greater Bear and who was likewise placed into the sky by Zeus. Another myth commemorates two bears who saved the infant Zeus from his father Kronos. When he later placed them in the sky, he flung them up by their tails, explaining these unnaturally long bear tails.\n"
"\n"
"Its most prominent object is Polaris, the Pole Star. In our era, it is less than a degree from the pole which makes it a very important navigational aid, but, due to precession, in antiquity there was no bright star right on the celestial pole."
msgstr ""
"_小熊座_，可能对应着卡利斯托之子阿卡斯——其母作为大熊已被宙斯安置于星空，或许阿卡斯也获得了同样的殊荣。另有一则神话说，曾有两头熊从父亲克洛诺斯手中救下了婴儿宙斯。后来，当宙斯将它们升为星座时，是抓着尾巴将它们抛上天空的，这便解释了为何这两只熊都拖着不合自然规律的长长尾影。\n"
"\n"
"小熊座最著名的星体是*北极星*。在我们的时代，它距离天北极不足一度，这使其成为极其重要的导航标志。然而，由于岁差的缘故，在古代并没有明亮的恒星恰好位于天球北极点上。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Dragon
msgid ""
"Greek mythology names several dragons. Eratosthenes identifies _Draco_ as Ladon, the snake-like dragon which protected the golden apples in the garden of the Hesperides. It was killed by Hercules who can be seen stepping on the dragon's head.\n"
"\n"
"The constellation winds around the Northern Ecliptical Pole, close to which we can observe a planetary nebula, the Cat's Eye. The star alpha Draconis, or *Thuban*, was closest to the Northern Celestial Pole when the Egyptians built their pyramids, and could have acted as their polar star."
msgstr ""
"希腊神话中记载着多条龙。根据埃拉托斯特尼的记述，_天龙座_被视为蛇形龙怪拉冬，曾守护赫斯珀里得斯圣园中的金苹果。它最终被赫拉克勒斯所杀，从星空中可见英雄正踏于龙首之上。\n"
"\n"
"该星座蜿蜒盘绕于北黄极周围，其附近可观测到一个行星状星云——猫眼星云。天龙座α星，即*右枢*，在埃及人建造金字塔的年代曾是距离北天极最近的恒星，很可能在当时充当过他们的极星。\n"
"\n"
"天龙座明亮的深空天体不多，最著名的是行星状星云猫眼星云。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Hercules
msgid ""
"Hercules, or the Kneeler, was a Greek hero, a son of Zeus with Alkmene. When his half-sister Athena tried to put him on Hera's breast, his biting caused Hera to push him away, and Hera's milk spilled all over the sky, creating the Milky Way. Hercules had to fulfill 12 major labours and countless other fights and adventures.  In the northern sky, he is actually upside-down, with his head, *Ras Algethi* next to the head of Ophiuchus, *Rasalhague*, and he is seen to trample on the head of Draco, the dragon. \n"
"\n"
"Hercules hosts the magnificent globular cluster Messier 13, and a smaller one, Messier 92."
msgstr ""
"_武仙座_，即赫拉克勒斯，亦称跪姿者，是希腊神话中的英雄，宙斯与阿尔克墨涅之子。当其同父异母的姐姐雅典娜试图将他置于赫拉胸前时，他的啃咬使赫拉猛然推开他，赫拉的乳汁溅洒苍穹，化为银河。赫拉克勒斯必须完成十二项伟业及无数次搏斗与冒险。在北天星图中，他实为倒置之姿——其首星*帝座*紧邻蛇夫座头部*候星*，可见他正践踏着天龙座之首。\n"
"\n"
"武仙座内蕴藏壮丽的球状星团  Messier 13，以及较小的  Messier 92。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Serpent Bearer
msgid ""
"The Serpent Bearer, _Ophiuchus_, also called _Serpentarius_, resembles a man"
" holding Serpens, the snake, in his hands. He is standing on Scorpius, and "
"with his legs he is in fact crossing the ecliptic. Some people therefore "
"call it the 13th zodiacal constellation, but the Zodiac still only has 12 "
"signs, for practical purposes of it being just a coordinate system. His "
"head, *Rasalhague*, is adjacent to the head of Hercules, *Ras Algethi*."
msgstr ""
"_蛇夫座_，亦称持蛇者，其形象宛如一位手擎巨蛇（即巨蛇座）的男子。他双足立于天蝎座之上，腿部实际横跨黄道。因此，有人称其为第十三个黄道星座，但出于实际应用考量（黄道本质仅为坐标系），传统黄道十二宫体系仍维持十二星座。其头部*侯*星与武仙座头部*帝座*相邻。\n"
"\n"
"蛇夫座距离银心不远，因此有很多球状星团，其中6个是梅西叶天体。蛇夫座ρ附近的星云复合体是绚丽多彩的*星空调色盘*的一部分，一直延伸到天蝎座。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Serpent
msgid ""
"The Serpent is the only constellation which nowadays comes in two parts, the"
" serpent's head and tail. Its central part is held by Ophiuchus, the Serpent"
" Bearer, and therefore those stars are counted belonging to that "
"constellation."
msgstr ""
"_巨蛇座_是现今唯一被分割为两部分的星座——蛇头与蛇尾。其中段由持蛇者蛇夫座掌控，因此该区域的星辰被划归蛇夫座所属。\n"
"巨蛇座有很多深空天体，著名的有M5球状星团，M16鹰星云。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Boötes
msgid ""
"This figure is described either as cow shepherd moving behind the seven oxen"
" (*septemtriones*) according to the Romans, or in Greek tradition of "
"*Arktophylax*, as figure related to the Greater Bear. Ptolemy described its "
"brightest star, *Arcturus*, as not belonging to the actual shape but as "
"bright star lying between his knees. Starting with the atlas of Polish "
"astronomer Jan Hevelius in the 17th century, Boötes leads the Hunting Dogs "
"on leashes."
msgstr ""
"_牧夫座_，在罗马传说中被描述为跟随*七牛星*（septemtriones）移动的牧牛人，而在希腊传统中则被称为“阿耳克托菲拉克斯”（Arktophylax），是与大熊座相关的守护者。托勒密曾记载其最亮的*大角星*并不属于该星座本体，而是悬于牧夫双膝之间的亮星。自17世纪波兰天文学家赫维留的星图始，牧夫座便被描绘为执绳牵曳猎犬的引路者。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Hunting Dogs
msgid ""
"The Hunting Dogs were introduced by Polish astronomer Jan Hevelius. In his atlas from 1687 he shows the dogs on a leash in the hands of Boötes, the Herdsman, maybe to chase the Greater Bear. \n"
"\n"
"The dim constellation hosts the magnificent Whirlpool Galaxy, Messier 51, and several other galaxies for small telescopes, and the bright globular cluster M3."
msgstr ""
"_猎犬座_由波兰天文学家约翰·赫维留引入。在其1687年的星图中，他将这两只猎犬描绘为系于**牧夫座**手中的缰绳之上，或许意在追逐大熊。\n"
"\n"
"在这片黯淡的星座中，却蕴藏着壮丽的涡状星系 M51 、数个适合小型望远镜观测的其他星系，以及明亮的球状星团 M3。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Triangle
msgid ""
"The Triangle has been associated with a lot of things, like the Greek uppercase letter Delta, the Nile delta, or the Island of Sicily.\n"
"\n"
"_Triangulum_ hosts one of the closest and brightest galaxies, Messier 33, called the Pinwheel."
msgstr ""
"_三角座_在历史上曾被赋予多种象征意义：如希腊大写字母Δ、尼罗河三角洲，或是西西里岛的轮廓。\n"
"\n"
"该星座拥有离我们最近、最明亮的星系之一—— M33三角座星系，亦被称为“风车星系”。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Ram
msgid ""
"_Aries_, the Ram, is the first of the twelve constellations of the Zodiac "
"which mark the area of the apparent paths of the Sun, Moon and the planets. "
"When the Zodiac system was invented, the stars stood roughly within the "
"respective signs. Over two thousand years of precessional movement along the"
" ecliptic has caused a shift which moved the actual star figures about one "
"full sign further towards the east."
msgstr ""
"_白羊座_作为黄道十二宫的首个星座，标记着太阳、月亮及行星视运行轨迹的区域。黄道体系创立之初，群星大致居于各自对应的宫位。然而历经两千余年的岁差运动，实际星象已沿黄道东移约一个完整宫位。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Bull
msgid ""
"_Taurus_, the front part of a bull, is one of the most conspicuous figures of the zodiac. The wide open star cluster of the Hyades form the V-shaped head with the red eye (which is itself not a member of the Hyades cluster), and the ends of two long horns are marked by moderately bright stars. On its back, the most famous of all open star clusters, the Pleiades, can be seen. Although named the Seven Sisters, most observers can see six or eight stars. The Hyades and Pleiades form the Golden Gate of the Ecliptic, through which all planets, the Sun and Moon usually pass. Occasionally, the Moon can occult the Pleiades. \n"
"\n"
"Taurus may have already been known to Paleolithic Europeans. A Cave painting in Lasceaux shows an Aurochs with a cluster of stars in its back."
msgstr ""
"_金牛座_以公牛的前半身为形象，是黄道带中最显眼的星座之一。疏散星团*毕星团*构成V形的牛头，其红色牛眼（毕宿五本身并非该星团成员）熠熠生辉，两支长角的末端则由中等亮度的星辰标定。牛背之上悬挂着所有疏散星团中最著名的*昴星团*。虽被称为“七姐妹”，但多数观测者实际可见六或八颗星。毕星团与昴星团共同形成“黄道金门”，所有行星、太阳与月亮通常都经此区域运行。月球偶尔会掩食昴星团。\n"
"\n"
"金牛座的观测历史可能追溯至旧石器时代的欧洲。法国拉斯科洞穴壁画中曾出现一头背驮星群簇的原始野牛图案。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Twins
msgid ""
"The zodiacal constellation of _Gemini_, the Twins, commemorates Kastor and Polydeukes, or Castor and Pollux. Queen Leda of Sparta gave birth to uneven twins, Castor fathered by her husband, King Tyndareos, and Polydeukes allegedly fathered by Zeus who had approached her in the shape of a beautiful swan, which made only Polydeukes immortal. The otherwise inseparable twins joined Hercules on Jason's voyage on the ship Argo. Castor was fatally wounded in a battle. Polydeukes pled to his divine father to let him die with his brother. Instead, Zeus placed both into the sky, where they jointly can be seen immortalized in the sky or go below the horizon into the underworld. \n"
"\n"
"Gemini is host to a fine open cluster (M35) and the Eskimo planetary nebula."
msgstr ""
"黄道星座_双子座_，其形象源自一对双生子——卡斯托尔与波吕丢刻斯（即北河二与北河三）。斯巴达王后勒达诞下这对异父兄弟：卡斯托尔为其丈夫廷达瑞俄斯国王之子，而波吕丢刻斯相传是宙斯化为天鹅亲近勒达所生，故唯其拥有神性。这对形影不离的兄弟曾随伊阿宋搭乘阿尔戈号，与赫拉克勒斯一同远征。卡斯托尔在一场战役中受致命伤，波吕丢刻斯恳求父亲宙斯让他与兄弟同死。宙斯遂将二人共同升入星空，使他们能以不朽之姿并列于天际，亦能一同沉入地平线下的冥界。\n"
"\n"
"双子座拥有美丽的疏散星团 M35 以及行星状星云“爱斯基摩星云”。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Crab
msgid ""
"The zodiacal constellation of _Cancer_, the crab, used to stand along the northernmost part of the ecliptic which defines the Tropic of Cancer. Precession has meanwhile moved it a full sign to the east. \n"
"\n"
"When Hercules was wrestling the Lernaean Hydra, the Crab appeared and bit him in the foot. Hercules killed it, but Hera, always opposing Hercules, placed it among the stars. \n"
"\n"
"As an aquatic animal, Cancer consists of only dim stars, but is host to a nice naked-eye open star cluster called Praesepe, the manger. Two dim stars resemble the northern and southern donkeys eating from it."
msgstr ""
"黄道星座_巨蟹座_，其形象为一只螃蟹。该星座曾位于黄道最北端，北回归线正由此界定。而今因岁差运动，其位置已东移整整一个宫位。\n"
"\n"
"当赫拉克勒斯与勒耳那水蛇搏斗时，这只螃蟹突然出现并咬住他的脚踵。赫拉克勒斯将其击杀，但向来与他为敌的赫拉女神却把螃蟹升为星辰。\n"
"\n"
"作为水生动物形象，巨蟹座仅由暗星组成，却拥有一个肉眼可见的美丽疏散星团——“鬼星团”（亦称马槽星团）。有两颗暗星恰似在此进食的南北二驴，更添趣味。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lion
msgid ""
"The lion, or _Leo_, is a large and conspicuous zodiacal constellation that was already known to the Babylonians. The Greeks identified it with the Nemean Lion which was killed by Hercules. \n"
"\n"
"Two trapezoids form body and head. Its main star, *Regulus* lies almost on the ecliptic. Leo is host to five fine Messier and several more galaxies."
msgstr ""
"_狮子座_是一个庞大而显著黄道星座，早在巴比伦时期就已为人所知。希腊人将其视为被赫拉克勒斯击杀的涅墨亚雄狮。\n"
"\n"
"两个梯形结构分别构成狮身与狮首。其主星*轩辕十四*几乎位于黄道上。狮子座内蕴藏五个美丽的梅西叶星系及若干其他星系。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Bernice's Hair
msgid ""
"Over the tuft of the Lion's tail we can see a loose cluster of dim stars. Ptolemy has described this as one of two asterisms added to his traditional 48 constellations. _Coma Berenices_ represents the Hair of Berenike II, consort of Ptolemy III Euergetes, which she had sacrificed for a safe return of her husband from war. It is the only constellation commemorating a historical person. \n"
"\n"
"The stars of Coma are indeed a loose open star cluster, and far behind, in the border region to Virgo, lies a region very rich in galaxies."
msgstr ""
"在狮子座尾鬃的上方，可见一片由暗星组成的疏散星团。托勒密曾将此类星群描述为其传统48星座之外增补的两个星群之一。_后发座_象征着托勒密三世王后贝勒尼基二世献祭的秀发——她为祈求丈夫征战平安归来而削发立誓。这是全天唯一纪念真实历史人物的星座。\n"
"\n"
"后发座的恒星确实是一个松散的疏散星团，在其与室女座的边界区域，有一个非常富饶的星系密集区域。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lesser Lion
msgid ""
"17th-century Polish astronomer Jan Hevelius filled several almost empty "
"regions between classical constellations with new figures in his atlas. _Leo"
" Minor_, the Lesser Lion, was one of them, residing between Leo and Ursa "
"Major."
msgstr ""
"17世纪波兰天文学家约翰·赫维留在其星图中，以新构星座填补了古典星座间的若干空旷天区。_小狮座_便是其中之一，它静伏于狮子座与大熊座之间的星空。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Maiden
msgid ""
"The large zodiacal constellation of _Virgo_, the Maiden, spans more than one and a half zodiacal signs. Since the times of her Babylonian origins, she is associated with fertility and holds an ear of grain in her hand, marked by its brightest star *Spica*. \n"
"\n"
"There are plenty of Messier Galaxies and many dimmer ones in the Virgo galaxy cluster and more generally the Virgo-Coma area."
msgstr ""
"_室女座_作为庞大的黄道星座，其区域横跨逾一个半黄道宫位。自巴比伦文明起源以来，她便与丰饶之神紧密相连，手中持有的麦穗由最亮星*角宿一*标定。\n"
"\n"
"其星群中蕴藏大量梅西叶星系，而室女座星系团乃至更广阔的室女-后发座天区，更散布着无数较暗弱的星系。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Scales
msgid ""
"The scales were known to Babylonian astronomy. The same stars were also seen as the claws of the Scorpion, which was the dominant interpretation in Greek antiquity. Later, the Romans re-established the scales as own constellation, commemorating the scales of Astraea, goddess of justice. \n"
"\n"
"The autumnal equinox point is called First Point of Libra, but this refers to the Zodiacal Sign. This point nowadays is near the head of Virgo."
msgstr ""
"_天秤座_的星象在巴比伦天文学中已有记载。同一片星域也曾被视为天蝎之螯——这曾是古希腊时期的主流解读。后来，罗马人将其重新确立为独立星座，以纪念正义女神阿斯特莱亚的天平。\n"
"\n"
"秋分点被称为“天秤宫第一点”，但这特指黄道宫位体系。如今秋分点实际位于室女座头部附近（天球赤道与黄道的交点因岁差持续西移）。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Scorpion
msgid ""
"When Orion boasted to Artemis that he could kill every animal on earth, she sent the scorpion to kill Orion. Both were raised to the stars by Zeus and placed on opposite sides of the sky. \n"
"\n"
"The constellation's brightest star is *Antares*, the \"counter-Mars\", named after its reddish color. A fan of stars radiating towards the west further extend towards the scales which used to be its claws, and a long curved tail extends towards the south-east, ending in a conspicuous sting.\n"
"\n"
"Scorpius is host to a few fine globular clusters, M4 and M80, and several open star clusters. It covers some of the brightest parts of the Milky Way."
msgstr ""
"_天蝎座_是一只毒蝎。当俄里翁向阿尔忒弥斯扬言能杀尽世间所有生灵时，她便派遣毒蝎终结了俄里翁的性命。宙斯将二者双双升入星空，并置于天穹两端永不相见。\n"
"\n"
"该星座最亮的*心宿二*（Antares，意为“火星之敌”）因色泽赤红得名。向西延伸的扇状星流曾被视为其螯钳（后演化为天秤座），而向东南蜿蜒的长尾末端，可见一道显赫的毒刺。\n"
"\n"
"天蝎座覆盖银河系中某些最为明亮的区域，拥有数个漂亮的球状星团（如 M4 与 M80）及若干疏散星团（如M6，M7，NGC 6231）。围绕心宿二的巨大的红色反射星云，是*星空调色盘*的一部分。*星空调色盘*是由反射星云、发射星云、暗星云和球状星团组成的绚丽多彩的天区，一直延伸到蛇夫座。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Archer
msgid ""
"_Sagittarius_, the Archer, is commonly depicted as centaur, half-man and half-horse. \n"
"\n"
"The Archer lies around the center of the Milky Way, therefore this area is rich with open and globular star clusters, bright and dark clouds. The bright Messier objects M8 (the Lagoon Nebula), M17 (the Omega Nebula) or M20 (the Trifid Nebula) are always worth a look, but there are more."
msgstr ""
"_人马座_常被描绘为半人半马的射手的形象。\n"
"\n"
"银河系中心位于人马座中，因此该区域富含疏散星团与球状星团，亮星云与暗星云。梅西叶天体有15个，明亮的梅西叶天体如M8（礁湖星云）、M17（奥米茄星云）或M20（三叶星云），以及更多的迷人天体都值得观察。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Capricornus
msgid ""
"The Sea-Goat constellation is of Babylonian origin and is depicted, as the name says, as \"having horns like a goat\", with the back of the body in shape of a fish tail. In antiquity it used to stand along the southernmost part of the ecliptic which defines the Tropic of Capricorn. Precession has meanwhile moved the stars a full sign to the east, so that the Zodiacal First point of Capricorn lies near the western edge of the constellation of Sagittarius.\n"
"\n"
"Capricornus includes one bright globular cluster, Messier 30."
msgstr ""
"_摩羯座_源于古巴比伦，它的形象是生有山羊角，又长了个鱼尾巴的动物。在古代，该星座曾位于黄道最南端，此处即定义了摩羯座回归线。由于岁差运动，如今这些恒星已整体东移一个星宫，使得摩羯宫的黄道起点现今位于人马座的西缘附近。\n"
"\n"
"摩羯座内包含一个明亮的球状星团 Messier 30。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Water Bearer
msgid ""
"_Aquarius_, the Water Bearer goes back to the Babylonian god Ea, bringer of fresh water. It is commonly depicted as man pouring water from a water jar which arches down into the mouth of the Southern Fish.\n"
"\n"
"In 1846, Johann Galle discovered the planet Neptune close to where now we see the border to Capricornus.\n"
"\n"
"The Water Bearer hosts three Messier objects: the two globular clusters M2 and M72, and the open cluster M73. \n"
"In addition, it shows two prominent planetary nebulae: The large Helix Nebula, and much smaller Saturn nebula."
msgstr ""
"_宝瓶座_（亦称持水者）可追溯至巴比伦的淡水之神埃阿。其形象常被描绘为手持水瓶倾倒水流之人，水弧径直落入南鱼座的口中。\n"
"\n"
"1846年，约翰·戈特弗里德·伽勒正是在宝瓶座与摩羯座边界附近发现了海王星。\n"
"\n"
"宝瓶座包含三个梅西叶天体：两个球状星团 M2 与 M72 ，以及一个疏散星团 M73 。此外，它还拥有两个著名的行星状星云：巨大的螺旋星云和微小的土星状星云。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Fishes
msgid ""
"The zodiacal constellation of _Pisces_, the Fishes, is located around where the Sun is on March equinox, the beginning of spring in the Northern hemisphere, a point commonly named the First Point of Aries. Since the time the Zodiac was defined as coordinate system of twelve zodiacal signs, the name-giving constellations have moved one full sign to the west by the precession of earth's axis. \n"
"\n"
"The two fishes are connected by a band of Babylonian origin. According to Hyginus, Aphrodite and Eros fled from the monster Typhon, jumped into the Euphrates river and were transformed into fishes. Ovid tells a similar story around their Roman counterparts, Venus and Cupid, who were not transformed, but saved by riding on the backs of two helpful fishes. In both stories the fishes are then placed into the sky, the band expressing their connectedness. \n"
"\n"
"The Fishes can be seen as two ovals of dim stars with a large V-shaped band knotted near the neck of Cetus. Its deep-sky highlight certainly is Messier 74, the Phantom Galaxy."
msgstr ""
"_双鱼座_位于春分点附近（约3月20日太阳所在位置，北半球春季起始点），该点常被称为“白羊宫第一点”。自黄道十二宫被确立为坐标系以来，因地球轴心岁差运动，实际星座已西移整整一个宫位。\n"
"\n"
"两条鱼由源自巴比伦传统的丝带相连。据希吉努斯记载，阿佛洛狄忒与厄洛斯为躲避怪物堤丰，跳入幼发拉底河化为双鱼；奥维德则讲述了对应的罗马神话版本：维纳斯与丘比特并未化身鱼类，而是骑着两条援救之鱼脱离险境。两则传说皆以双鱼升天作结，星带象征其紧密相连的羁绊。\n"
"\n"
"双鱼座可视为两个由暗星组成的椭圆，其宽阔的V形星带在鲸鱼座颈部附近交汇成结。该星座深空天体的亮点无疑是 M74 幻影星系。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Water Snake
msgid ""
"_Hydra_, the Water Snake, is the largest of all constellations. Its origins go back to Babylonian times. The Greek mythology knows a story where Corvus, the Crow, was sent out with the Crater (the Cup) to fetch water for Apollo. The crow was distracted by a fig tree, the fruits of which it wanted to eat. When it finally returned, it brought a snake from the well, claiming it was the cause of the delay. Apollo, discovering the lie, threw Corvus, the Crater and Hydra into the sky.\n"
"\n"
"Hydra hosts three Messier objects: the Southern Pinwheel galaxy (M83), a globular cluster nearby (M68) and the open cluster M48. Furthermore, there is the Ghost of Jupiter planetary nebula, and many fainter galaxies."
msgstr ""
"_长蛇座_作为全天最大的星座，其渊源可追溯至巴比伦时期。希腊神话中有一段著名传说：阿波罗派遣乌鸦（乌鸦座）持杯（巨爵座）取水，乌鸦却被无花果树吸引，耽于啄食果实。最终它带着从井中捞起的水蛇归来，谎称是水蛇导致延误。识破谎言的阿波罗遂将乌鸦、水杯与长蛇一同抛向苍穹。\n"
"\n"
"长蛇座包含三个梅西叶天体：南风车星系（M83）、其附近的球状星团M68以及疏散星团M48。此外还有木魂星云与众多暗弱星系。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Cup
msgid ""
"This is the cup, or _crater_, which was handed to Corvus, the crow, by "
"Apollo to fetch water. When the crow finally returned with an excuse that a "
"water snake caused its delay, Apollo did not believe the story and flung all"
" three, Corvus, Crater and Hydra into the sky."
msgstr ""
"_巨爵座_，即由阿波罗交给乌鸦科沃斯去打水的杯子。直到乌鸦最终带着借口返回，声称是因水蛇才耽搁了行程，阿波罗不信其言，便将乌鸦座、巨爵座与长蛇座一同抛向了天际。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Crow
msgid ""
"_Corvus_, the crow, was sent out by Apollo to fetch water with Crater, the "
"cup. When the crow finally returned with an excuse that a water snake caused"
" its delay, Apollo did not believe the story and flung all three, Corvus, "
"Crater and Hydra into the sky, arranging them so that the crow could not "
"drink from the cup."
msgstr ""
"_乌鸦座_，即受阿波罗派遣，携杯子前去取水的乌鸦。当乌鸦最终归来，借口说水蛇导致其延误，阿波罗不信此言，便将乌鸦座、巨爵座与长蛇座一同抛向天际，并特意安排其位置，使乌鸦永世不得从杯中饮水。\n"
"乌鸦座拥有著名的星系触须星系——一对正在合并的交互作用星系NGC 4038和NGC 4039。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Northern Crown
msgid ""
"The Northern Crown, or _Corona Borealis_, commemorates the crest or similar bridal adornment of Ariadne, it was originally not a solid golden king's crown as shown here.  In one version of the legend, Dionysos gave a wreath to Ariadne, daughter of King Minos of Crete, who handed it over to Theseus as he went into the labyrinth to kill the Minotaur, and the wreath's light helped Theseus finding the way out again. Theseus took Ariadne to Naxos but abandoned her. Dionysos found and married her, throwing her bridal crown into the heavens.\n"
"\n"
"The Northern Crown features interesting variable stars: the cataclysmic variable T Coronae Borealis and the prototype R Coronae Borealis which occasionally drops by many magnitude in brightness, obscured by its own dust clouds."
msgstr ""
"_北冕座_原为纪念阿里阿德涅的头冠或类似的新娘饰物，最初并非如图所示那般是坚固的黄金王冠。在一则神话版本中，酒神狄俄尼索斯曾将一顶花冠赠予克里特国王米诺斯之女阿里阿德涅。当忒修斯进入迷宫斩杀弥诺陶洛斯时，阿里阿德涅将此冠交予他，冠冕的光芒助忒修斯重寻出路。事后忒修斯带阿里阿德涅至纳克索斯岛，却将她遗弃。狄俄尼索斯发现并娶她为妻，将她新娘的头冠抛向了天际。\n"
"\n"
"北冕座拥有引人注目的变星：激变变星北冕座T，以及原形星北冕座R——后者偶尔会因自身尘埃云的遮蔽而亮度骤降多等。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Southern Crown
msgid ""
"The Southern Crown, or _Corona Australis_, should be seen more as wreath "
"than as crown. It may belong to either Sagittarius or Centaurus. It can be "
"seen as distinct ring of faint stars south of the \"Teapot\" asterism of "
"Sagittarius."
msgstr ""
"_南冕座_，其形象更似花环而非冠冕，其归属或在人马座与半人马座之间未有定论。在人马座“茶壶”星群以南的夜空中，可见由暗星组成的清晰环状结构。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Eagle
msgid ""
"Aquila is the Eagle which carried the thunderbolts of Zeus and was sent out to bring the pretty boy Ganymede to the Olymp to serve as cupbearer. In another context Ptolemy placed Antinoos, the deceased favourite of emperor Hadrian, among the stars beside the eagle. For the Romans it was _Vultur volans_, the flying vulture, as opposed to _vultur cadens_, their interpretation of Lyra.\n"
"\n"
"The main star, *Altair*, is one star of the famous Summer Triangle asterism, together with *Vega* in Lyra and *Deneb* in Cygnus. \n"
"\n"
"The Pioneer 11 space probe is heading towards &lambda; Aquilae, but don't hold your breath - it is expected to pass the star in about 4 million years."
msgstr ""
"_天鹰座_象征着为宙斯携带雷电、并奉命将美少年甘尼米德携往奥林匹斯担任侍酒者的雄鹰。在另一种星象传统中，托勒密将哈德良皇帝逝去的宠臣安提诺乌斯置于天鹰之侧的星群间。罗马人则视其为“飞翔的秃鹫”，以区别于对应天琴座的“坠落的秃鹫”。\n"
"\n"
"其主星*牛郎星* 与天琴座的*织女星*、天鹅座的*天津四* 共同构成著名的夏季大三角。\n"
"\n"
"先锋11号探测器正朝向天鹰座λ星航行——不过请不必屏息以待，预计它将在约四百万年后才会经过。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lyre
msgid ""
"According to Greek mythology, the young god Hermes stole a herd of Apollo's sacred cows. From a hollowed-out turtle shell and cow gut, he created the first _lyra_ which he gave to Apollo in compensation for the theft. The Greeks saw the constellation as commemorating the lyre of Orpheus, the famous singer. Later, the Roman author Hyginus saw the lyre of Theseus and connected it to nearby Hercules. Romans also saw _vultur cadens_ or the falling vulture, in contrast to _vultur volans_, our Aquila or Eagle.\n"
"\n"
"The brightest star *Vega* is of magnitude 0.0. It is one star of the famous Summer Triangle asterism, together with *Altair* in Aquila and *Deneb* in Cygnus.   The nearby star epsilon is the famous double-double star, two close double stars observable in one eyepiece field. On the other end of the lyre, the famous Ring Nebula (M57) can be seen. And don't forget to visit globular cluster M56."
msgstr ""
"_天琴座_是_里拉琴_根据希腊神话，年轻的神祇赫尔墨斯偷走了阿波罗的一群圣牛。他用掏空的龟甲与牛肠制作了第一把_里拉琴_，并将其赠予阿波罗作为盗窃的补偿。希腊人将这个星座视为纪念著名歌手俄耳甫斯的里拉琴。后来，罗马作家希吉努斯将其解读为忒修斯的里拉琴，并与邻近的武仙座相联系。罗马人也曾将此星座视为“坠落的秃鹫”，以区别于“飞翔的秃鹫”（即天鹰座）。\n"
"\n"
"最亮的恒星*织女星*视星等为0.0等。它是著名的夏季大三角星群之一，另两颗分别是天鹰座的*牛郎星*与天鹅座的*天津四*。附近的epsilon星是著名的“双双星”——两对紧密的双星可在同一望远镜视场中被观测到。在天琴的另一端，可见著名的环状星云（M57）。此外，别忘了探访球状星团 M56。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Swan
msgid ""
"_Cygnus_, The Swan, is a large and conspicuous constellation right in the northern Milky Way. Its central part is also called Northern Cross, but its outstretched wing ends show the elegant curve of a large flying bird with long neck. In Greek mythology, it can be interpreted as one of several swans, among them Zeus who disguised himself as swan to seduce Leda, who then gave birth to the Twins, or Orpheus, who was transformed into a swan after his murder and placed into the sky next to his instrument, the lyre. In another interpretation, the three birds, Cygnus, the flying eagle or vulture (Aquila) and falling eagle or vulture (Lyra) could represent the Stymphalian birds which nearby Hercules had to fight as one of his twelve labours.\n"
"\n"
"The brightest star *Deneb* in its tail is one star of the famous Summer Triangle asterism, together with *Altair* in Aquila and *Vega* in Lyra. Deneb is one of the most luminous stars of its spectral class known. It is 2600 light years away. The Swan's head star, *Albireo* is a pretty color-contrast binary star, a bright orange star with a blue companion. &chi; Cygni is a Mira-type variable sometimes visible in the swan's neck.\n"
"\n"
"With its position right in the Milky Way, Cygnus hosts a multitude of star clusters and bright and dark nebulae. Famous examples are the North America Nebula and the Veil supernova remnant. The Milky Way itself is seen to be split by the Cygnus Rift, a dark molecule cloud."
msgstr ""
"_天鹅座_是横跨北天银河的一个巨大而醒目的星座。其中心部分亦被称为“北十字”，但展翅的末端与修长的脖颈共同勾勒出一只飞翔的天鹅的优雅曲线。在希腊神话中，它可以被解读为多只天鹅中的一只——可能是宙斯，他曾化身天鹅诱惑勒达，后者随后诞下双子座；亦或是俄耳甫斯，他在遇害后化为天鹅，被安置于天际，紧邻其乐器天琴座。另一种解读认为，这三只鸟——天鹅、飞翔的鹰或秃鹫（天鹰座）以及坠落的鹰或秃鹫（天琴座），可能象征了武仙座附近的赫拉克勒斯在其十二项任务中必须对付的斯廷法利斯湖怪鸟。\n"
"\n"
"其尾部的亮星*天津四*是著名“夏季大三角”星群之一，另两颗分别是天鹰座的*牛郎星*与天琴座的*织女星*。天津四是已知同类光谱型恒星中最明亮的恒星之一，距离我们约2600光年。天鹅头部恒星*辇道增七*是一对美丽的色彩对比双星，由一颗明亮的橙色恒星与一颗蓝色伴星组成。天鹅座χ是一颗蒭藁型变星，有时可见于天鹅颈部。\n"
"\n"
"由于恰好位于银河之中，天鹅座拥有众多星团、亮星云与暗星云。著名的例子包括北美星云和超新星遗迹面纱星云。银河本身在此处被天鹅座裂缝——一片暗分子云——分割开来。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Altar
msgid ""
"The Altar with offerings in fire and smoke is usually depicted with the smoke going to the south.\n"
"\n"
"The constellation lies along the Milky Way south of Scorpius and has rich star fields, including a large globular cluster."
msgstr ""
"_天坛座_即燃烧着供奉之火、烟雾缭绕的祭坛，通常被描绘为烟雾飘向南方的形象。\n"
"\n"
"该星座位于天蝎座以南的银河带中，拥有丰富的星场，包括一个大型球状星团。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Dolphin
msgid ""
"In a story told by Roman poet Ovid, the musician Arion was on a return voyage from a successful concert tour to Sicily and Italy. The crew of his ship envied his amassed fortunes and wanted to kill him. Arion was granted a last wish, and he started singing, then jumped into the sea where a dolphin had been attracted by his music. The dolphin brought him back to the shore, and was placed into the heavens with nine stars.\n"
"\n"
"The dolphin, or _Delphinus_, is a small but conspicuous shape between Aquila and Cygnus."
msgstr ""
"根据罗马诗人奥维德所述的故事，音乐家阿里翁在结束了西西里与意大利的成功巡演后乘船返航。船上的水手们觊觎他积累的财富，企图杀害他。阿里翁被允许完成最后一个心愿，于是他开始歌唱，随后跳入大海——一只被他的音乐吸引而来的海豚正游弋其间。海豚将他送回了海岸，后来便被置于天际，化为九颗星辰。\n"
"\n"
"_海豚座_是一个小巧而醒目的星座，坐落于天鹰座与天鹅座之间。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Eridanus
msgid ""
"The large constellation of the river Eridanus flows from its origin near *Rigel* in a winding curve towards the south. When Phaethon, son of Helios, failed to control his father's Sun wagon, Zeus had to throw a thunderbolt and Phaethon plunged burning into the Eridanus river.\n"
"\n"
"The brightest star *Archernar* is too far south to have been observed from the Mediterranean, so usually *Acamar* used to be the final observable star of the river."
msgstr ""
"巨大的_波江座_从*参宿七*附近发源，蜿蜒向南流淌。当太阳神赫利俄斯之子法厄同失控驾驶其父的日辇时，宙斯不得不投掷雷霆，致使法厄同燃烧着坠入波江。\n"
"\n"
"其最亮的*水委一*因位置过于偏南，无法从地中海地区观测到，因此传统上常将*天园六*视为这条星河可观测的终点。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Arrow
msgid ""
"The distinct Arrow, or _Sagitta_, is the third smallest constellation. It may be an arrow shot by Hercules against the Eagle devouring the liver of Prometheus, or against the Stymphalian birds (Cygnus, Aquila, Lyra).\n"
"\n"
"Its deep-sky highlight is the globular cluster Messier 71."
msgstr ""
"_天箭座_，是全天第三小的星座。它可能是赫拉克勒斯射向啄食普罗米修斯肝脏的鹰（天鹰座），亦或是射向斯提法利亚鸟类（天鹅座、天鹰座、天琴座）的箭。\n"
"\n"
"其深空天体亮点是球状星团 M71。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Southern Fish
msgid ""
"_Piscis Austrinus_, the Southern Fish, goes back to a Babylonian fish "
"constellation. It may be parent to the two fishes of the zodiacal "
"constellation of the Fishes. It is a mostly dim constellation. The only "
"moderately bright star is *Fomalhaut*, the mouth of the fish, which is often"
" drawn to swallow the water poured by Aquarius from his water jar."
msgstr ""
"_南鱼座_可追溯至一个巴比伦鱼形星座。它或许是黄道星座双鱼座中两条鱼共同的源头。该星座主要由暗星组成，唯一一颗中等亮度的恒星是位于鱼嘴处的*北落师门*——在星图中，它常被描绘为正在吞饮宝瓶座从水罐中倾泻而流水。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Keel
msgid ""
"_Carina_, or the Keel of the Ship, is part of the antique constellation Argo, which commemorates the ship of Jason and the Argonauts who sailed to Kolchis in search of the Golden Fleece. \n"
"\n"
"In the 1750s, French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille proposed to break apart the huge Argo constellation and created three separate parts. The other parts are Vela, the sails, and Puppis, the stern. This decision was only finalized in 1930 when the International Astronomical Union decided about the official constellation borders.\n"
"\n"
"Its brightest star, *Canopus*, is the second brightest fixed star and lies close to the south pole of the ecliptic, and therefore is an important navigational star for interplanetary spacecraft.\n"
"\n"
"Three cross-like asterisms can be seen in Carina: The False Cross which in cloudy nights may have decepted navigators in search of the Southern Cross, the Diamond Cross, and the Shadow Cross. \n"
"\n"
"Carina lies along the Milky Way and therefore includes a multitude of deep-sky objects like star clusters and gas clouds. Most prominent is the region about eta Carinae, a star system with huge luminosity which from 1837 to the 1850s experienced a \"Great Eruption\", temporarily becoming the second-brightest star in the sky.  \n"
"\n"
"To the south of it we find the Southern Pleiades open star cluster."
msgstr ""
"_船底座_，即船的龙骨，是古代星座南船座的一部分。南船座纪念的是伊阿宋率领阿尔戈英雄们前往科尔基斯寻找金羊毛时所乘的船只。\n"
"\n"
"18世纪50年代，法国天文学家尼古拉-路易·德·拉卡伊提议将巨大的南船座拆分，形成三个独立部分。其余两部分分别是船帆座和船尾座。这一划分直至1930年国际天文学联合会确定官方星座边界时才最终确立。\n"
"\n"
"其最亮的恒星*老人星*是夜空中第二亮的恒星，位置靠近黄道南极，因此成为星际航天器导航的重要基准星。\n"
"\n"
"船底座内可见三个十字形星群：伪十字星（在多云的夜晚曾误导航海者将其误认为南十字座）、钻石十字星和暗影十字星。\n"
"\n"
"船底座位于银河带上，因此包含众多深空天体，如星团与气体云。最著名的是船底座η星区域，这个恒星系统拥有极高的光度，在1837年至19世纪50年代期间曾发生\"大爆发\"，一度成为天空第二亮的恒星。其周边的巨大而明亮的弥漫星云 NGC 3372 也被称为船底座η星云或船底座大星云，它看起来比猎户座大星云更为明亮。\n"
"\n"
"船底座有多个目视可见的疏散星团。在船底座星云南侧可见明亮的疏散星团南天昴宿星团。船底座星云东北侧则是许愿井星团，星座中西部的钻石星团皆肉眼可见，球状星团NGC 2808也相当明亮。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Stern
msgid ""
"_Puppis_, the stern of the ship, is the largest part of the former constellation Argo. The other parts are Carina, the keel, and Vela, the sails. The Argo took Jason and the Argonauts to Kolchis in search of the Golden Fleece.\n"
"\n"
"Puppis lies along the Milky Way and contains several prominent open clusters. In the northern part we find three Messier clusters, M46, M47 and M93. The planetary nebula NGC2438 appears to lie inside M46, but is a foreground object."
msgstr ""
"_船尾座_是古代南船座拆分后最大的组成部分，其余两部分分别为船底座（龙骨）和船帆座（船帆）。南船座曾载着伊阿宋与阿尔戈英雄们前往科尔基斯寻找金羊毛。\n"
"\n"
"船尾座位于银河带中，包含数个显著的疏散星团。其北部可见三个梅西叶星团：M46、M47与M93。行星状星云NGC2438看似位于M46内部，实则为前景天体。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Sails
msgid ""
"_Vela_ are the sails of the former constellation Argo. The other parts are Carina, the keel, and Puppis, the stern. The Argo took Jason and the Argonauts to Kolchis in search of the Golden Fleece.\n"
"\n"
"_Vela_ lies along the Milky Way and shows several interesting deep-sky objects. Most notably the Eight-Burst or Southern Ring Planetary Nebula, and the globular cluster NGC 3201."
msgstr ""

#. Description of Modern constellation Centaur
msgid ""
"According to Roman poet Ovid, the figure commemorates the centaur Chiron who had instructed Hercules and several other heroes. Chiron was accidentally poisoned by an arrow shot by Hercules. \n"
"\n"
"Centaurus is a large and conspicuous figure. The bright stars alpha and beta Centauri are commonly named \"Pointers\" as they indicate the Southern Cross which in antiquity were seen as the Centaur's hind legs.  Alpha is the nearest bright star and actually a multiple star system. One component is even closer to the Sun but only visible in telescopes: Proxima Centauri. Its light takes only 4.3 years to reach us. \n"
"\n"
"The large constellation lies along the Milky Way and therefore contains many open and several globular star clusters, most notably the largest in the sky, Omega Centauri."
msgstr ""
"_半人马座_是一个庞大而醒目的星座。根据罗马诗人奥维德的记载，这个形象是为了纪念曾教导赫拉克勒斯及其他多位英雄的半人马喀戎。喀戎不幸被赫拉克勒斯误射的毒箭所伤。\n"
"\n"
"其亮星半人马座α与β常被称为\"指极星\"，因它们指向南十字座——在古代星图中，南十字座曾被视作半人马的后腿。半人马座α是距离地球最近的亮星，实际为一个聚星系统。其中一颗成员星距离太阳更近，但仅能通过望远镜观测：即比邻星。它的光线仅需4.3年便可抵达地球。\n"
"\n"
"这个巨大星座横贯银河，因此包含许多疏散星团及数个球状星团，最著名的是全天最大的球状星团——半人马座ω星团。珠宝盒星团，奔鸡星云亦适合探索。明亮的星系半人马座A以巨大的尘埃带闻名。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Wolf
msgid ""
"_Lupus_, the Wolf, used to be an unspecified wild animal against which Centaurus was fighting, or, alternatively, a wineskin. \n"
"\n"
"In 1006, Lupus was host to the brightest supernova in written history."
msgstr ""
"_豺狼座_，在历史上曾被视为被半人马座攻击的未具体指明的野兽，另有一说其形象原为酒囊。\n"
"\n"
"公元1006年，豺狼座区域内曾爆发有记载以来最明亮的超新星。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Southern Cross
msgid ""
"Early European seafarers separated four conspicuous stars from the hind legs"
" of Centaurus to form _Crux_, the Southern Cross. It was first published on "
"a celestial globe from 1589 by Jacob van Langren and Petrus Plancius and was"
" accepted as an important guide for navigation and also spiritual guidance."
msgstr ""
"早期的欧洲航海者将半人马座后腿部位四颗显著的恒星分离出来，构成了_南十字座_。该星座于1589年由雅各布·范·朗伦和彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯首次刊载于天球仪上，后被公认为航海导航与精神指引的重要标志。\n"
"\n"
"煤袋星云是天空中最著名与突出的暗星云，主体位于南十字座。疏散星团珠宝盒星团肉眼可见。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Southern Triangle
msgid ""
"The simple constellation of _Triangulum Australe_ was introduced by Dutch-"
"Flemish cartographer Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe published by Jacob"
" van Langren in 1589."
msgstr "_南三角座_这一简明星座，由荷兰-佛兰芒制图师彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯引入，并首次标注于雅各布·范·朗伦于1589年出版的天球仪上。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Dove
msgid ""
"The Dove has been introduced by Dutch-Flemish cartographer Petrus Plancius in the early 1590s next to the great ship Argo. It represents the Dove returning to Noah with an olive branch, showing the end of the deluge.\n"
"\n"
"The constellation contains the Solar antapex, meaning the Solar system moves away from this direction."
msgstr ""
"_天鸽座_由荷兰-佛兰芒制图师彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯于16世纪90年代初创立，位于巨大的南船座旁。其形象象征衔着橄榄枝飞回诺亚方舟的鸽子，预示大洪水的终结。\n"
"\n"
"该星座方向为太阳背点所在，即太阳系正朝与此相反的方向运动。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Fly
msgid ""
"Originally this was introduced as _Apis_, the Bee, by Petrus Plancius on a "
"celestial globe from 1598. Abbé de la Caille renamed it to its current name "
"_Musca_, the Fly."
msgstr ""
"该星座最初由彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯于1598年的天球仪上创立，命名为_蜜蜂座_。后由拉卡伊神父更名为现称_苍蝇座_。\n"
"\n"
"煤袋星云一角位于苍蝇座，暗饰带星云在煤袋星云南部，是很适合双筒望远镜观赏的暗星云。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Bird of Paradise
msgid ""
"_Apus_, the Bird of Paradise, was introduced by Petrus Plancius on a "
"celestial globe from 1598, based on observations by Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser "
"and Frederick de Houtman."
msgstr ""
"_天燕座_由彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录创立，并首次标注于1598年的天球仪上。它的形象是极乐鸟。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Chameleon
msgid ""
"A _chamaeleon_ was introduced by Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe from "
"1598, based on observations by Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de "
"Houtman."
msgstr ""
"_蝘蜓座_，形象为变色龙，由彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录创立，并首次标注于1598年的天球仪上。\n"
"\n"
"蝘蜓座内遍布分子云。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Swordfish
msgid ""
"_Dorado_ was introduced by Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe from 1598, "
"based on observations by Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman. "
"Usually translated as Goldfish, and later also named Swordfish, it was named"
" after the Mahi-Mahi or dolphinfish, a predatory fish often hunting the "
"Flying Fish that you can see nearby."
msgstr ""
"_剑鱼座_由彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录创立，并首次标注于1598年的天球仪上。该星座常被译作\"金鱼座\"，后亦称\"旗鱼座\"，其名称源于鬼头刀鱼（亦称鲯鳅）——这种掠食性鱼类常捕食邻近可见的飞鱼座所象征的飞鱼。\n"
"银河系的伴星系大麦哲伦云的大部分位于剑鱼座天区内，其余部分则在山案座天区内。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Flying Fish
msgid ""
"Early European seafarers reported swarms of fish flying out of the water to "
"escape their predators. _Volans_, the Flying Fish, was introduced by Petrus "
"Plancius on a celestial globe from 1598, based on observations by Pieter "
"Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman. It is a common prey of the "
"Doradus, or Goldfish. Both can be seen near Carina, the ship's keel of the "
"old constellation Argo."
msgstr ""
"早期欧洲航海家曾记载成群的飞鱼跃出水面以躲避捕食者。_飞鱼座_由彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录创立，并首次标注于1598年的天球仪上。它是剑鱼座（亦称金鱼座）常见的猎物。两者皆可在古代南船座的龙骨——船底座附近观测到。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Crane
msgid ""
"The Crane, or _Grus_, is one of the four \"Southern Birds\" introduced by "
"Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe from 1598, based on observations by "
"Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman. The others are the "
"Peacock, Phoenix, and the Toucan."
msgstr ""
"_天鹤座_是彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录，于1598年的天球仪上创立的“南方四鸟”星座之一。其余三座分别为孔雀座、凤凰座和杜鹃座。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Peacock
msgid ""
"_Pavo_, the Peacock, is one of the four \"Southern Birds\" introduced by "
"Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe from 1598, based on observations by "
"Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman. The others are the Crane, "
"Phoenix, and the Toucan."
msgstr ""
"_孔雀座_是彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录，于1598年的天球仪上创立的“南方四鸟”星座之一。其余三座分别为天鹤座、凤凰座和杜鹃座。\n"
"孔雀座有天空中第三亮的球状星团NGC 6752"

#. Description of Modern constellation Phoenix
msgid ""
"The Phoenix is the largest of the four \"Southern Birds\" introduced by "
"Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe from 1598, based on observations by "
"Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman. The others are the "
"Peacock, the Crane, and the Toucan."
msgstr ""
"_凤凰座_是“南方四鸟”中最大的星座，由彼得勒斯·普朗修斯依据彼得·德克斯宗·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录，于1598年首次绘制在天球仪上。其余三座分别为孔雀座、天鹤座及杜鹃座。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Toucan
msgid ""
"_Tucana_, the Toucan, is the smallest of the four \"Southern Birds\" "
"introduced by Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe from 1598, based on "
"observations by Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman. The others"
" are the Peacock, Phoenix, and the Crane. Originating from a Dutch "
"expedition to the East Indies, it actually shows a Hornbill, while the name "
"was taken from the bird in the American Tropics."
msgstr ""
"_杜鹃座_是彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录，于1598年的天球仪上创立的“南方四鸟”星座中最小的一座。其余三座分别为孔雀座、凤凰座和天鹤座。该星座源于荷兰东印度群岛远征队的观测，其图像实际描绘的是犀鸟，而名称却取自美洲热带地区的巨嘴鸟,中国将其翻译为杜鹃座\n"
"\n"
"银河系的伴星系小麦哲伦云位于杜鹃座最南端，杜鹃座47位于小麦哲伦云侧，是全天第二亮的球状星团，NGC 362也是杜鹃座的球状星团。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lesser Water Snake
msgid ""
"_Hydrus_, the Male, or Lesser Water Snake, was introduced by Petrus Plancius"
" on a celestial globe from 1598, based on observations by Pieter Dirkszoon "
"Keyser and Frederick de Houtman. It seems to continue the wiggle line formed"
" by the Eridanus river. A line connecting its brightest star, beta, and the "
"Southern Cross can guide you to the Southern Celestial Pole."
msgstr ""
"_水蛇座_，即雄性小水蛇，由彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼的观测记录创立，并首次标注于1598年的天球仪上。其蜿蜒的形态仿佛延续了波江座河流的曲线。连接其最亮星β星与南十字座的连线可指引观测者找到南天极。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Indian
msgid ""
"The Indian, _Indus_, was introduced by Petrus Plancius on a celestial globe "
"from 1598, based on observations by Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de"
" Houtman made on a Dutch expedition to the Eastern Indies. It is therefore "
"likely to show a native from the region called East India by the European "
"discoverers, or South-Eastern Asia today."
msgstr ""
"印第安座（_Indus_）由彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯根据彼得·迪尔克松·凯泽与弗雷德里克·德·豪特曼在荷兰东印度群岛远征期间的观测记录创立，并首次标注于1598年的天球仪上。因此，该星座很可能描绘的是被欧洲发现者称为\"东印度\"地区（即现今东南亚）的原住民形象。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Giraffe
msgid ""
"On a celestial globe from 1612, Flemish-Dutch cartographer Petrus Plancius "
"introduced a few new constellations to fill the voids. One of them was this "
"large but inconspicuous constellation of _Camelopardalis_, the Giraffe, "
"between Ursa Major and Cassiopeia."
msgstr ""
"在1612年的天球仪上，佛兰芒-"
"荷兰制图师彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯为填补空白区域引入了一些新星座。其中之一便是位于大熊座与仙后座之间这片广阔却不起眼的天区——_鹿豹座_，即长颈鹿。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Unicorn
msgid ""
"The large but inconspicuous constellation of _Monoceros_, the Unicorn, between Orion and Canis Minor, made its first appearance on a celestial globe from 1612 by the Flemish-Dutch cartographer Petrus Plancius.\n"
"\n"
"While it does not have bright stars, telescope owners will like to visit a few fine open star clusters, and especially the Rosette Nebula."
msgstr ""
"_麒麟座_是位于猎户座与小犬座之间广阔却不起眼的天区——，由佛兰芒-荷兰制图师彼得鲁斯·普兰修斯于1612年首次标注在天球仪上。它的形象是独角兽。\n"
"\n"
"虽然其恒星亮度不高，但望远镜观测者可以在此寻访数个美丽的疏散星团，尤其值得探访的是玫瑰星云。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lynx
msgid ""
"The constellation of Lynx was introduced by Polish astronomer Jan Hevelius "
"in the late 17th century. You need the eyes of a Lynx to see it."
msgstr ""
"_天猫座_由波兰天文学家扬·赫维留于17世纪末创制。需具山猫般的锐目，方能觅其踪迹。\n"
"\n"
"天猫座的NGC 2419是距离银河系中心最遥远的银河系球状星团之一，被称为星际漫游者。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Shield
msgid ""
"_Scutum_, the constellation of the shield, was introduced by Polish "
"astronomer Jan Hevelius in the late 17th century to pay homage to his king, "
"Jan Sobieski."
msgstr ""
"_盾牌座_由波兰天文学家扬·赫维留斯于17世纪末创立，以向其国王扬·索别斯基致敬。\n"
"\n"
"盾牌座可以找到疏散星团 M11（也叫野鸭星团） 和M16"

#. Description of Modern constellation Fox
msgid ""
"Originally introduced as the constellation of _Vulpecula cum Ansere_, the Fox with the Goose, by Polish astronomer Jan Hevelius in the 17th century, nowadays we only see the little fox here. \n"
"\n"
"It is host to the famous Dumbbell planetary nebula, M27, and the Coathanger asterism, both visible in binoculars."
msgstr ""
"_狐狸座_星座最初由波兰天文学家扬·赫维留斯于17世纪创立，原名为_Vulpecula cum Ansere_（狐狸与鹅座），如今我们仅在此处见到小狐狸的形象。\n"
"\n"
"这片天区孕育着著名的哑铃星云（M27）与衣架星群，二者皆可通过双筒望远镜观测。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Lizard
msgid ""
"The constellation of _Lacerta_, the Lizard, was introduced by Polish "
"astronomer Jan Hevelius in the late 17th century."
msgstr "_蝎虎座_意为蜥蜴，由波兰天文学家扬·赫维留斯于17世纪末创立。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Sextant
msgid ""
"Polish astronomer Jan Hevelius placed the _sextans_, one of his "
"observational instruments, into the sky in his atlas of 1687. This was not "
"the mirror sextant later used for marine navigation!"
msgstr ""
"波兰天文学家扬·赫维留斯在其1687年的星图中将_六分仪座_——其观测仪器之一——置于星空。需要注意的是，这并非后来用于航海导航的反射式六分仪！"

#. Description of Modern constellation Air Pump
msgid ""
"The Air Pump, a scientific development of the 17th century, was formed as "
"constellation _Antlia Pneumatica_ by French astronomer-geodesist Abbé "
"Nicolas-Louis de la Caille in the mid-18th century."
msgstr ""
"_唧筒座_指的是气泵。作为17世纪的科学发明，由法国天文学兼测地学家尼古拉-路易·德·拉卡伊神父于18世纪中期塑造，原名为_Antlia "
"Pneumatica_（气动泵）。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Engraving Tool
msgid ""
"This dim and small constellation was introduced as _Caelum Sculptorium_ by "
"French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille in the 1750s. It "
"commemorates an engraver's chisel, an essential tool for mapmaking."
msgstr ""
"_雕具座_是暗淡的小星座，由法国天文学家尼古拉-路易·德·拉卡伊神父于18世纪50年代创立，原名为_Caelum "
"Sculptorium_（雕具凿）。其形象为雕刻师的凿子，是地图制作的重要工具。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Drawing Compass
msgid ""
"French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille introduced _Circinus_, the"
" Drawing Compass, to join Triangulum Australe and Norma as scientific "
"instruments for geometrical construction."
msgstr "法国天文学家尼古拉-路易·德·拉卡伊神父将_圆规座_（绘图圆规）引入星空，使其与南三角座、矩尺座共同构成几何绘图的科学仪器星座系列。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Carpenter's Square
msgid ""
"A carpenter's square, helpful to draw right angles was important enough for "
"Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille to depict it as _Norma_ among his new "
"constellations on the southern hemisphere, adjacent to other draughtsman's "
"tools, Triangulum Australe and Circinus."
msgstr "木工角尺作为绘制直角的重要工具，其意义足以促使拉卡伊神父将其塑造为南半球新星座中的_矩尺座_，并与另两种绘图工具——南三角座与圆规座相邻。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Furnace
msgid ""
"_Fornax_, a chemical oven was one of the scientific instruments placed into the southern sky by French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille. \n"
"\n"
"With only five stars brighter than 5th magnitude, it is better known for its richness in galaxies."
msgstr ""
"_天炉座_，指一种化学熔炉，是法国天文学家尼古拉-路易·德·拉卡伊神父置于南天星空中的科学仪器之一。\n"
"\n"
"该星座仅有五颗亮于5等的恒星，但以其丰富的星系分布而闻名。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Clock
msgid ""
"In 1756, French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille placed "
"_Horologium_, a pendulum clock with seconds hand, among the stars. An "
"accurate clock of this kind was an important scientific instrument of his "
"era, the Age of Enlightenment."
msgstr ""
"1756年，法国天文学家尼古拉-"
"路易·德·拉卡伊神父将一座带有秒针的钟摆计时器——_时钟座_——安置于群星之间。此类精密计时器正是其所处启蒙时代的重要科学仪器。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Microscope
msgid ""
"French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille created 14 new "
"constellations in the southern sky in which he mostly commemorated "
"scientific instruments of his time, the mid-18th century. _Microscopium_, "
"the Microscope, just south of Capricornus, consists of dim stars only."
msgstr "_显微镜座_是法国天文学家尼古拉-路易·德·拉卡伊神父于18世纪中叶在南天创建了14个新星座之一。它位于摩羯座正南方，仅包含暗星。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Telescope
msgid ""
"Next to the Microscope, French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille "
"placed _Telescopium_ in his mid-18th century maps which introduced 14 new "
"constellations, mostly commemorating scientific instruments. In his own "
"imagination it was a long-focal-length aerial telescope, but later the "
"constellation was cut back to its present size. It has only seven stars "
"brighter than magnitude 5."
msgstr ""
"在显微镜座旁，法国天文学家尼古拉-"
"路易·德·拉卡伊神父于18世纪中期绘制的星图中增设了_望远镜座_。该星图共引入14个新星座，大多为纪念科学仪器而设。在拉卡伊的构想中，此星座原指长焦距的折射式望远镜，但后来其范围被缩减至现今的规模。该星座仅包含七颗亮度高于5等的恒星。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Table Mountain
msgid ""
"French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille observed the southern sky "
"in the mid-18th century from the Cape of Good Hope. He commemorated the "
"Table Mountain in his constellation of _Mensa_, which includes the Large "
"Magellanic Cloud resembling the cloud \"table cloth\" frequently forming "
"around the top of the mountain."
msgstr ""

#. Description of Modern constellation Octant
msgid ""
"The Octant was a tool for marine navigation, similar to the sextant, "
"developed by John Hadley in 1730. In his series of constellations "
"commemorating scientific instruments, French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis "
"de la Caille placed _Octans_ right next to the Southern Celestial Pole. It "
"only shows dim stars."
msgstr ""
"八分仪是一种类似六分仪的航海导航工具，由约翰·哈德利于1730年发明。在其纪念科学仪器的系列星座中，法国天文学家尼古拉-"
"路易·德·拉卡伊神父将“八分仪座”直接设置在南天极旁。因南天极在其内部，中国将其译为_南极座_。该星座仅由暗淡的恒星组成。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Painter's Easel
msgid ""
"The full name of this constellation was _Equuleus Pictoris_, or the Painter's Easel, when French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille introduced it in the mid-18th century. The name was shortened to _Pictor_.\n"
"\n"
"In 1983, the IRAS Infrared Astronomical Satellite discovered a debris disk around the star Beta Pictoris. Later observations even showed two disks and several exoplanets."
msgstr ""
"法国天文学家尼古拉-路易·德·拉卡伊神父于18世纪中叶创立该星座时，其完整名称为_Equuleus Pictoris_（画家画架）。后简称为_绘架座_。\n"
"\n"
"1983年，IRAS红外天文卫星在绘架座β星周围发现了一个碎屑盘。后续观测甚至揭示出两个盘状结构及数颗系外行星。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Reticle
msgid ""
"A constellation _Rhombus_ had already been introduced in the early 17th "
"century. More than a century later, French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de "
"la Caille changed it to the present constellation of _Reticulum_, again "
"commemorating a scientific instrument. The rhomboidal reticle, or net, was a"
" device placed in the eyepiece's focal plane to allow more precise "
"measurements."
msgstr ""
"早在17世纪初，\"菱形座\"便已作为星座被提出。一个多世纪后，法国天文学家尼古拉-"
"路易·德·拉卡伊神父将其改为如今的_网罟座_，再次以此纪念一种科学仪器。菱形网丝（即十字丝）是一种安装在目镜焦平面上的装置，用于实现更精确的测量。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Sculptor
msgid ""
"French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille created the _Apparatus Sculptoris_, the sculptor's studio in the 1750s, later shortened to Sculptor. \n"
"\n"
"While the constellation only hosts dim stars, deep-sky observers will enjoy galaxies: The Sculptor Galaxy (NGC 253), NGC 55 or even the Sculptor Dwarf galaxy."
msgstr ""
"法国天文学家尼古拉·路易·德·拉卡伊神父于18世纪50年代创立了“雕塑家工作室”（拉丁语原名 _Apparatus Sculptoris_），后简称为_玉夫座_。\n"
"\n"
"该星座虽仅有暗星，但深空观测者将可畅游星系之趣：玉夫座星系（NGC 253）、NGC 55乃至玉夫座矮星系皆在此列。"

#. Description of Modern constellation Mariner Compass
msgid ""
"French astronomer Abbé Nicolas-Louis de la Caille created 14 new "
"constellations in the southern sky in which he mostly commemorated "
"scientific instruments of his time, the 18th century. _Pyxis_, the Mariner "
"Compass, can be seen as a valuable addition to the old Ship Argo, which de "
"la Caille has however broken up into three pieces: Carina (the keel), Vela "
"(the sails), and Puppis (the stern)."
msgstr ""
"法国天文学家尼古拉·路易·德·拉卡伊于18世纪在南天星空创制了14个新星座，其中多以当时科学仪器命名。_罗盘座_作为对古老南船座的珍贵补充，可见于天际——尽管拉卡伊已将南船座拆解为三部分：船底座、船帆座及船尾座。"

