#. Norse (Edda) sky culture name
msgid "Norse (Edda)"
msgstr "北欧（埃达）"

#. Norse (Edda) sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"In the 13th century, Snorri Sturluson provided the most comprehensive "
"documentation of myths from Old Norse culture that we know of today in his "
"Edda. In this sky culture, the Eddic myths are to be brought into the sky in"
" the form of constellations. Since there are no records of constellations "
"from this time and region, the reconstruction of these constellations is not"
" always certain (in some cases even speculative). In our visualisations we "
"follow various literary scholars who found parallels to Norse mythology in "
"the Edda."
msgstr ""
"13世纪时，斯诺里·斯蒂德吕松（Snorri "
"Sturluson）在其著作《埃达》（Edda）中，为我们今天所知的古诺尔斯文化神话提供了最全面的记载。在这一星空文化中，埃达神话以星座的形式被映射到天空之中。由于当时该地区并未留下任何关于星座的直接记录，这些星座的复原往往并不确定——在某些情况下甚至带有推测性质。在我们的可视化呈现中，我们参考了多位文学学者的研究，他们曾在《埃达》中发现与北欧神话相呼应的天象关联。"

#. Norse (Edda) sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The Eddic myths were widespread in the North Germanic cultural area, which encompasses present-day Scandinavia (Denmark, Norway, Sweden, Iceland). They were written down in the 13th century in Iceland, predominantly in two literary works, the Prose Edda and the Poetic Edda, this way representing the most important sources of our knowledge on Norse mythology. The culture referred to here therefore includes the North Germanic peoples from the 13th century and earlier. An important factor in observing the sky at this latitude is the brightness of the midnight sun in summer. During several weeks, the sky at Iceland's latitude does not get dark or only for a very short time, which severely limits the possibility of observing stars during this period. Given the fact that Snorri’s Edda was written in Iceland and under the assumption that some of the myths describe celestial phenomena, this plays an important role in the localization of assumed constellations: for instance, the modern constellation of Scorpius, the Scorpion, is hardly visible, so, it won't be identified with any Norse constellation. More information and discussion of each one of the (hypothetical) constellations will be given in the All Skies Encyclopaedia.\n"
"\n"
"### Sky\n"
"\n"
"The origin of the Eddic myths remains disputed (Jonsson 1994 [#3], p. 41). In recent decades, some attempts have been made to map the sagas of the Edda onto constellations in the night sky. However, this fact does not negate Snorri's statement that the phenomena he describes are quite literally located in the sky (Sigurdson 2022 [#7], p. 239). Snorri Sturluson provides a systematic, sequential description of mythological cosmogony in his Edda. Gangleri, the protagonist of Gylfaginning, is told that in the beginning lights were assigned a staðr (place) and a path in the sky. Their movements marked the passage of time. The Sun is given salir (halls) and the stars staðir (places) by the gods (Æsir). These are the key terms in Gylfaginning for celestial locations and phenomena (Sigurdson 2022 [#7], p. 239). After that several places in the sky are described, some of which can be found here as constellations. The sky itself was created by the Æsir from the skull of the primeval giant Ymir, whom they had slain (Sturluson 2017 [#9], p. 21). Subsequently, they took sparks that had flown from Muspelheim, the realm of fire, and set them in the sky as stars (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 22).\n"
"\n"
"### Constellations\n"
"\n"
"Although many Eddic constellations are based on on many assumptions and guesses, those that are also mentioned in the Rimtöl-gloss (Úlfs Keptr, Asar Bardagi, Fiskikarlar) are described with more certainty. The only constellations the Edda specifically describes as stars are Aurvandils tá and Þjaza augu. \n"
"\n"
"### Moon and Sun\n"
"\n"
"Due to the geographical latitude at which many inhabitants of ancient Scandinavia lived, summers are very bright and winters very dark. At the latitude of Iceland, there are even several weeks in summer during which hardly any stars can be observed at night. Likewise, there are several weeks in winter when the sun is barely visible and the moon rises only a few degrees above the horizon (or not at all, depending on its orbit's position). Under these unreliable conditions, it is unlikely that Old Norse peoples maintained detailed calendars based on the sun or the moon. In Eddic mythology, the sun and the moon are personified as the children of Mundilfari. The son, Mani, steers the course of the moon, and the daughter, Sol, that of the sun (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 24). Neither may ever stop on their paths, for both are pursued by wolves that wish to devour them. The wolf chasing the sun is called Sköll, and the one chasing the moon is called Hati. When Ragnarök begins, the downfall of the gods, both will be devoured by the wolves (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 25).\n"
"\n"
"### Planets\n"
"\n"
"Due to the lack of reliable sources, planets are excluded from this sky culture. \n"
"\n"
"### Zodiac\n"
"\n"
"Considering that some parts of the zodiac are not visible at all throughout the year at Iceland’s latitude, and that almost no constellations can be observed during the summer, no attempt has been made here to include a zodiac. The same goes for a lunar system.\n"
"\n"
"### Milky Way\n"
"\n"
"In this model, the Milky Way serves as the embodiment of the world tree Yggdrasil. This ash tree is the largest and best of all trees, and its branches spread across the entire world (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 28). It has three roots, and beneath each one is a spring. Several literary scholars believe that locating Yggdrasil in the sky would be useful for understanding the topography of the Eddic myths. However, this is contradicted by the description of animals living in the tree (Lorenz 1984 [#5], p. 241). If we assume that the animals mentioned, such as squirrels and eagles, are also celestial objects/ constellations, then Yggdrasil forms a super-constellation containing these constellations, and equating it with the Milky Way becomes rather inevitable. Sigurdson (2022) [#7] and Jonsson (1994) [#3] also believe that this translucent white tree in the sky should be understood as a mythical analogue of the Milky Way (Sigurdson 2022 [#7], p. 238). \n"
"\n"
"![](illustrations/MilkyWay_Edda.png)"
msgstr ""
"埃达神话曾广泛流传于北日耳曼文化区域，这一区域涵盖现今的斯堪的纳维亚地区（丹麦、挪威、瑞典、冰岛）。这些神话于13世纪在冰岛被记载下来，主要收录于两部文学作品——《散文埃达》与《诗体埃达》中，由此成为我们了解北欧神话最重要的资料来源。因此，这里所指的文化包括13世纪及更早时期的北日耳曼民族。在此纬度观测天空的一个重要因素是夏季午夜太阳的明亮程度。每年有数周时间，冰岛所处纬度的天空不会完全变暗，或仅短暂陷入黑暗，这严重限制了在此期间观测星辰的可能性。考虑到斯诺里（Snorri）的《埃达》写于冰岛，且假设部分神话描述了天体现象，这一点在推定星座定位时起着重要作用：例如，现代星座中的天蝎座（Scorpius）在此地几乎不可见，因此它不太可能与任何北欧星座相对应。关于每个（推测的）星座的更多信息与讨论，将在《全天百科全书》中提供。\n"
"\n"
"### 天空\n"
"\n"
"埃达神话的起源至今仍有争议（Jonsson 1994 [#3]，第41页）。近几十年来，学界曾多次尝试将埃达中的传奇故事映射到夜空中的星座上。然而，这并未否定斯诺里（Snorri）的陈述，即他所描述的现象确实字面意义上位于天空之中（Sigurdson 2022 [#7]，第239页）。斯诺里·斯图鲁松（Snorri Sturluson）在其《埃达》中对神话宇宙起源进行了系统而连续的描述。在《欺骗古鲁菲》中，主人公甘格勒里（Gangleri）被告知，最初光芒被赋予了天空中的位置（staðr）和路径。它们的运动标志着时间的流逝。诸神（Æsir）为太阳设立了宫殿（salir），为星辰指定了位置（staðir）。这些是《欺骗古鲁菲》中描述天体位置和现象的关键术语（Sigurdson 2022 [#7]，第239页）。随后，文中描述了天空中的多个地点，其中一些在此被视作星座。天空本身是由诸神用他们杀死的原始巨人尤弥尔（Ymir）的头颅创造而成（Sturluson 2017 [#9]，第21页）。之后，他们取来从火之国穆斯贝尔海姆（Muspelheim）飞溅出的火花，将它们置于天空中成为星辰（Sturluson 2017 [#8]，第22页）。\n"
"\n"
"### 星座\n"
"\n"
"尽管许多埃达星座是基于大量假设和猜测，但那些在《Rimtöl-gloss》中亦有提及的星座（如Úlfs Keptr、Asar Bardagi、Fiskikarlar）则被描述得更为确定。《埃达》中明确描述为星辰的星座仅有奥万迪尔之趾（Aurvandils tá）和提亚兹之眼（Þjaza augu）。\n"
"\n"
"### 月亮与太阳\n"
"\n"
"由于古斯堪的纳维亚许多居民所处的地理纬度，夏季极为明亮，冬季则非常黑暗。在冰岛纬度，夏季甚至有数周时间几乎无法在夜间观测到星辰。同样，冬季也有数周时间太阳几乎不可见，月亮仅在地平线上方升起几度（或根本不出，取决于其轨道位置）。在这种不稳定的条件下，古诺尔斯民族不太可能维持基于太阳或月亮的详细历法。在埃达神话中，太阳和月亮被拟人化为蒙迪尔法里（Mundilfari）的子女。儿子玛尼（Mani）掌管月亮的轨迹，女儿苏尔（Sol）掌管太阳的轨迹（Sturluson 2017 [#8]，第24页）。两者皆不可停歇，因为它们都被企图吞噬它们的狼追逐。追逐太阳的狼名为斯库尔（Sköll），追逐月亮的狼名为哈提（Hati）。当诸神黄昏（Ragnarök）来临时，两者都将被狼吞噬（Sturluson 2017 [#8]，第25页）。\n"
"\n"
"### 行星\n"
"\n"
"由于缺乏可靠资料来源，行星在此星空文化中不予纳入。\n"
"\n"
"### 黄道带\n"
"\n"
"考虑到黄道带的部分区域在冰岛纬度全年完全不可见，且夏季几乎观测不到任何星座，此处未尝试纳入黄道带。月球系统亦然。\n"
"\n"
"### 银河\n"
"\n"
"在此模型中，银河被视为世界树尤克特拉希尔（Yggdrasil）的化身。这棵梣树是所有树木中最大且最伟岸的，其枝干延伸至整个世界（Sturluson 2017 [#8]，第28页）。它有三条根，每条根下各有一处泉眼。多位文学研究者认为，将尤克特拉希尔定位于天空中有助于理解埃达神话的地形描述。然而，这与对居住在树中的动物的描述相矛盾（Lorenz 1984 [#5]，第241页）。如果我们假设所提及的动物（如松鼠和鹰）也是天体/星座，那么尤克特拉希尔便构成了一个包含这些星座的超大星座，将其等同于银河也就变得相当必然。西格松（Sigurdson 2022 [#7]）和琼森（Jonsson 1994 [#3]）也认为，天空中这棵半透明的白色之树应被理解为银河的神话对应物（Sigurdson 2022 [#7]，第238页）。\n"
"\n"
"![](illustrations/MilkyWay_Edda.png)"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Aurwandill's Toe
msgid ""
"Aurvandils tá (Aurwandill’s toe) is the toe of the hero Aurwandill, which "
"froze when he was carried by Thor across the icy river Eliwagar. Thor broke "
"off the toe, cast it into the sky, and thereby transformed it into an "
"asterism (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 111). Persson (2017) [#6] suggests Corona "
"Borealis as the corresponding constellation. On the one hand, its shape "
"resembles that of a toe; on the other, as a spring constellation, it allows "
"an interpretation of the toe as a symbol of the victory of spring over "
"winter (Persson 2017 [#6])."
msgstr ""
"奥万迪尔之趾（Aurvandils "
"tá）是英雄奥万迪尔（Aurwandill）的脚趾。当托尔（Thor）背负他跨越冰河埃利瓦格（Eliwagar）时，这只脚趾被冻僵。托尔将脚趾折断，抛向天空，从而将其化为一个星群（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. 111）。Persson (2017) [#6] 提出，北冕座（Corona "
"Borealis）是与之对应的星座。一方面，其形状类似脚趾；另一方面，作为一个春季星座，它可被解读为春天战胜冬天的象征（Persson 2017 "
"[#6]）。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Thiazi's Eyes
msgid ""
"Þjaza augu (Thiazi’s eyes) are the eyes of the giant Thiazi, who abducted "
"the goddess Idun. The Æsir fought and killed Thiazi, and when his daughter "
"sought revenge, Odin, as a sign of respect, cast Thiazi’s eyes into the sky,"
" transforming them into stars (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 83). There is no "
"concrete evidence as to which stars these might be, but the two bright and "
"closely positioned stars Castor and Pollux are obvious candidates."
msgstr ""
"提亚兹之眼（Þjaza "
"augu）是巨人提亚兹（Thiazi）的眼睛，他曾绑架女神伊登（Idun）。诸神（Æsir）与之战斗并杀死了提亚兹。当他的女儿前来复仇时，奥丁（Odin）出于敬意，将提亚兹的眼睛抛向天空，将其化为了星辰（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. "
"83）。关于这具体是哪两颗星，并无确凿证据，但明亮且位置接近的双星——北河二（Castor）与北河三（Pollux）——是显而易见的候选者。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Bifröst
msgid ""
"Bifrǫst (bifrost) is the bridge that extends from the Earth to the heavens "
"(Edda, 1997/2017, p. 26). The Æsir ride across Bifrǫst daily to the well of "
"Urðr at the World Tree and hold council there (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 29). "
"In literary scholarship, Bifrǫst is identified as a rainbow by day and as "
"the Milky Way by night (Persson [#6], 2017). However, the Milky Way is "
"already well represented by Yggdrasil, and the translation of Bifrǫst as "
"“shimmering road” (Persson [#6], 2017) could equally well be interpreted as "
"a stellar formation. The arc-shaped group of stars from Pegasus to Deneb in "
"the Milky Way closely resembles a bridge leading the Æsir to the well of "
"Urðr at Yggdrasil."
msgstr ""
"彩虹桥（Bifrǫst）是从大地通往天界的桥梁（《埃达》，1997/2017, p. "
"26）。诸神（Æsir）每日骑马跨越彩虹桥，前往世界树旁的乌尔德之泉（Urðr），并在那里举行会议（Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. "
"29）。在文学研究中，彩虹桥通常被解释为白日的彩虹与夜晚的银河（Persson [#6], "
"2017）。然而，银河在神话中已有世界树（Yggdrasil）作为其代表，且“Bifrǫst”一词本身可译为“闪烁之路”（Persson [#6], "
"2017），这同样可以被理解为一个星群。从飞马座延伸到天津四、位于银河中的那组弧形星群，其形态极似一座桥梁，引领诸神通向世界树旁的乌尔德之泉。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Heimdall's Castle
msgid ""
"Himinbjǫrg (Heimdall’s castle) is the structure standing on Bifröst and "
"inhabited by the Æsir Heimdall, who has keen eyesight and guards the bridge "
"against giants (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 39). The quadrilateral formed by "
"Algenib, Markab, Alpheratz, and Scheat at the long arc conveys a clear image"
" of a structure atop a bridge."
msgstr ""
"海姆贝尔格（Himinbjǫrg，即海姆达尔城堡）是一座立于彩虹桥（Bifröst）之上的建筑，由拥有敏锐视力、负责守卫此桥以防巨人侵袭的诸神之一——海姆达尔（Heimdall）居住（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. "
"39）。在长弧形的桥梁上，由壁宿一（Algenib）、室宿一（Markab）、壁宿二（Alpheratz）和室宿二（Scheat）四颗星构成的四边形，清晰地呈现出一座位于桥顶的建筑的意象。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Jaw of the Wolf
msgid ""
"Úlfs Keptr (jaw of the wolf) is a constellation mentioned in the Rimtöl "
"glosses and identified with the Hyades (Sigurðsson 2022  [#7], p. 241). "
"Wolves play a significant role in Old Norse mythology, as they are foretold "
"to devour the sun and moon at Ragnarök (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 25). The "
"Hyades lie along the moon’s path, and their V-shaped arrangement naturally "
"invites comparison with a jaw snapping at the moon. Holmberg (2022 [#2], p. "
"18) further proposes that this wolf-jaw constellation may already have been "
"recorded on the Rök Runestone in the early 9th century."
msgstr ""
"乌尔夫斯凯普特尔（Úlfs Keptr，意为狼颚）是一个在《Rimtöl》注释中提及的星座，被认定为毕星团（Hyades）（Sigurðsson "
"2022 [#7], p. 241）。狼在古诺尔斯神话中扮演着重要角色，预言中它们将在诸神黄昏（Ragnarök）吞噬太阳和月亮（Sturluson "
"2017 [#8], p. 25）。毕星团位于月球运行的路径上，其V形的排列方式自然让人联想到一张试图咬住月亮的颚部。Holmberg (2022 "
"[#2], p. 18) 进一步提出，这个狼颚星座可能早在9世纪初就已记录在罗克石碑（Rök Runestone）之上。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Thor's Chariot
msgid ""
"Þórs vagn (Thor’s chariot) is the chariot of the thunder god Thor, drawn by "
"two goats (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 35). Thor, alongside Odin, was one of the"
" principal deities in Old Norse mythology. Due to his strong connection to "
"weather, he was crucial not only for seafaring but also for agriculture "
"(Lorenz 1984 [#5], p. 308). The shape of a chariot formed by the brightest "
"stars of the Big Dipper lends itself well to association with Thor’s "
"chariot. The Rimtöl gloss also records the constellation under the name "
"Karlvagn or “man’s chariot” (Persson [#6], 2017)."
msgstr ""
"托尔之车（Þórs vagn）是雷神托尔（Thor）的战车，由两只山羊牵引（Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. "
"35）。托尔与奥丁（Odin）同为古诺尔斯神话中的主要神祇。由于他与天气的紧密关联，他不仅对航海至关重要，对农业也极为重要（Lorenz 1984 "
"[#5], p. "
"308）。由北斗七星最亮的恒星构成的车形轮廓，很容易让人联想到托尔的战车。《Rimtöl》注释亦将此星座记载为“Karlvagn”或“男子之车”（Persson"
" [#6], 2017）。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Freyja's Chariot
msgid ""
"Freyju vagn (Freyja’s chariot) is the chariot of the fertility goddess "
"Freyja, drawn by cats. When Freyja rides to a battlefield, she receives half"
" of the slain warriors, the other half going to Odin (Sturluson [#8] 2017, "
"p. 38). In the Rimtöl gloss, the small chariot in Ursa Minor is referred to "
"as Kvennavagn, or “woman’s chariot” (Persson [#6], 2017)."
msgstr ""
"弗蕾亚之车（Freyju "
"vagn）是生育女神弗蕾亚（Freyja）的战车，由猫牵引。当弗蕾亚乘车前往战场时，她会接收一半阵亡的战士，另一半则归奥丁所有（Sturluson "
"[#8] 2017, p. 38）。在《Rimtöl》注释中，小熊座中的小型车形星群被称为“Kvennavagn”，意为“女子之车”（Persson "
"[#6], 2017）。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Freyr's Sickle
msgid ""
"Freys sigð (Freyr’s sickle) belongs to the god Freyr, who governs rain and "
"sunshine and thus the fertility of the earth. He is invoked for a good "
"harvest (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 37). The star Spica (“ear of grain”) served"
" as a calendar star for sowing and harvest in various cultures and periods. "
"A constellation corresponding to a sickle located around Spica fits into Old"
" Norse mythology, as Freyr is depicted on an 11th-century runestone (Gotland"
" Runic Inscription 181). The depicted shape is an approximation, but it can "
"be traced through the brightness of the stars forming the sickle."
msgstr ""
"弗雷之镰（Freys sigð）属于弗雷（Freyr）神所有，他掌管雨水与阳光，因而主宰大地的丰饶。人们向他祈求丰收（Sturluson 2017 "
"[#8], p. "
"37）。角宿一（Spica，“麦穗”）这颗星在不同文化与时期都曾被用作指示播种与收获的历法星辰。一个位于角宿一附近、对应于镰刀的星座形象，很契合古诺尔斯神话的体系，因为弗雷神正是描绘于一块11世纪的如尼石刻（哥特兰如尼铭文181号）之上。此处描绘的镰刀形状是一个近似轮廓，但可以通过构成此镰刀的恒星的亮度加以辨识。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Thor
msgid ""
"Þórr (Thor) was, alongside Odin, a central deity in Norse mythology. The two"
" objects associated with him in the Edda are his hammer Mjöllnir and his "
"belt, which doubles his strength (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 35). The "
"constellation Orion was well known in the Middle Ages, and in various "
"cultures figures holding objects were interpreted within it. The three "
"bright belt stars are particularly prominent and could represent Thor’s belt"
" of strength. Objects interpreted elsewhere as a shepherd’s staff "
"(Babylonian) or a piece of leather (Greek) could here symbolize Thor’s "
"hammer."
msgstr ""
"托尔（Þórr）是与奥丁并列的北欧神话核心神祇。在《埃达》中，与他相关的两件物品是他的锤子米约尔尼尔（Mjöllnir）以及能使他的力量倍增的腰带（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. "
"35）。猎户座在中世纪已广为人知，并且在不同的文化中，人们常将其星群解读为手持物品的人物形象。其中三颗明亮的腰带星尤为突出，可以被视为托尔的力量腰带。而在其他文化中被解释为牧羊杖（巴比伦）或一块皮革（希腊）的星群部分，在此则可能象征着托尔的战锤。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation River Van
msgid ""
"Ván is the river that flows from the mouth of Fenris after the Æsir bound "
"him and inserted a sword into his jaws (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 44). Its "
"proximity to Thor in this model is notable, as wading through rivers is a "
"typical Thor motif (Lorenz [#5] 1984, p. 253)."
msgstr ""
"万恩河（Ván）是从芬里尔（Fenris）口中流出的河流，源于诸神（Æsir）将其捆绑并插入一把剑至其颚中（Sturluson 2017 [#8], "
"p. 44）。在此模型中，其与托尔位置相近这一点值得注意，因为涉水渡河是托尔的一个典型母题（Lorenz [#5] 1984, p. 253）。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation The Asar Battlefield
msgid ""
"Asar Bardagi (battlefield of the Æsir) is mentioned in the Rimtöl gloss and "
"equated with the constellation Auriga. The Edda recounts multiple battles "
"involving the Æsir and daily skirmishes among Odin’s warriors, the "
"einherjar, in Valhalla (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 51). Holmberg (2022 [#2], p."
" 21) suggests possible references to the early 9th-century Rök Runestone, "
"which also describes a battlefield, supporting the celestial interpretation."
msgstr ""
"阿萨巴达吉（Asar "
"Bardagi，意为诸神的战场）在《Rimtöl》注释中被提及，并被等同于御夫座（Auriga）。《埃达》记述了涉及诸神（Æsir）的多场战役，以及奥丁的勇士英灵战士（einherjar）在英灵殿（Valhalla）中每日发生的冲突（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. 51）。Holmberg (2022 [#2], p. 21) "
"提出，这可能指涉了同样描述了一处战场、年代可追溯至9世纪初的罗克石碑（Rök Runestone），从而支持了将这一名称解释为天空星象的观点。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Fishermen
msgid ""
"Fiskikarlar (the fishermen) is a constellation preserved in the Rimtöl "
"gloss. The name “fishermen” likely refers to the fishing episode in the "
"Edda, where Thor and the giant Hymir fish for the Midgard Serpent using the "
"head of the ox Himinhjǫrð (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 66). The legend predates "
"the Rimtöl gloss, recorded already in the 10th century (Krause 2010 [#4], p."
" 133). The identification of the constellation with Orion’s three belt stars"
" fits the stellar culture, as Thor is both part of the fishermen in the myth"
" and represented by the Orion constellation. Positioning the fishermen next "
"to the Midgard Serpent and the ox’s head is consistent with representing the"
" fishing episode in the sky."
msgstr ""
"菲斯基卡拉尔（Fiskikarlar，意为渔夫）是一个保存在《Rimtöl》注释中的星座。其名称“渔夫”很可能指代《埃达》中的捕鱼情节：托尔（Thor）与巨人希米尔（Hymir）以牛“希明赫约德”（Himinhrjǫð）的头为饵，垂钓中庭巨蛇（Midgard"
" Serpent）（Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 66）。这一传说早于《Rimtöl》注释的记录，在10世纪已有记载（Krause "
"2010 [#4], p. "
"133）。将该星座认定为猎户座三颗腰带星符合星象文化传统，因为托尔既是神话中渔夫的一员，其本身亦由猎户座代表。将渔夫星安置于中庭巨蛇和牛头星的旁边，也正对应着在天空中再现这一捕鱼故事。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Midgard Serpent
msgid ""
"Jormungandr (Midgard Serpent) is the serpent that spans the world in Eddic "
"myths. As Thor’s adversary, it appears in the fishing episode (Sturluson "
"2017 [#8], p. 66). It can be associated with a constellation similar to "
"Hydra, but in this model, stars visible from Iceland are used. The position "
"along the Milky Way is notable, as the dragon or snake Nidhögg lies beneath "
"a root of Yggdrasil and gnaws at it (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 28). In this "
"model, where the Milky Way represents Yggdrasil, Jormungandr could assume "
"Nidhögg’s role."
msgstr ""
"约尔曼冈德（Jormungandr），即米德加尔德（Midgard，即北欧神话九个世界中的中间世界，为人类居住的地方）巨蛇。是埃达神话中环绕世界的巨蛇。作为托尔（Thor）的宿敌，它出现在捕鱼的情节中（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. "
"66）。它可以被联系到一个类似长蛇座（Hydra）的星座，但在此模型中，使用的是从冰岛可见的恒星。其沿银河分布的位置值得注意，因为毒龙或巨蛇尼德霍格（Nidhögg）就位于世界树（Yggdrasil）的一条树根之下并啃噬着它（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. 28）。在此模型中，既然银河代表世界树，那么约尔曼冈德便可承担起尼德霍格的角色。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Ox Head
msgid ""
"Himinhjǫrð (ox’s head) is the largest ox in Hymir’s herd, which Thor beheads"
" to use as bait for fishing the Midgard Serpent (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. "
"65). The bright star Procyon, situated between Thor and the Midgard Serpent,"
" provides a suitable reference point."
msgstr ""
"希明赫约德（Himinhjǫrð，意为牛头）是希米尔（Hymir）牛群中最大的那头牛，托尔（Thor）将其斩首用作垂钓中庭巨蛇（Midgard "
"Serpent）的饵料（Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. "
"65）。位于托尔与中庭巨蛇之间的明亮恒星南河三（Procyon），提供了一个合适的参考点。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Ratatosk
msgid ""
"Rátatǫskr is the squirrel that scurries along the World Tree, carrying "
"messages between Nidhögg, the serpent, and the eagle (Sturluson 2017 [#8], "
"p. 30). Cassiopeia lies on the Milky Way between the constellations "
"representing the eagle and the serpent."
msgstr ""
"拉塔托斯克（Rátatǫskr）是沿世界树（World Tree）奔跑的松鼠，在毒蛇尼德霍格（Nidhögg）与鹰之间传递消息（Sturluson "
"2017 [#8], p. 30）。仙后座（Cassiopeia）位于银河之中，介于代表鹰和蛇的星座之间。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Eagle Giant
msgid ""
"Hræsvélgr (Hraesvelgr) is the giant in eagle form sitting at the edge of the"
" sky, generating wind through the beating of his wings (Sturluson 2017 [#8],"
" p. 33). The Edda also mentions an eagle perched in Yggdrasil (Sturluson "
"2017 [#8], p. 30). The constellation’s shape and position on the Milky Way "
"fit this model, and the eagle is visible in the early evening during autumn,"
" assigning Hraesvelgr a role as a sign of autumnal storms."
msgstr ""
"赫拉斯维尔格（Hræsvélgr）是以鹰形态端坐于天际边缘的巨人，其翅膀的扇动能产生风（Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. "
"33）。《埃达》亦提及有一只鹰栖于世界树（Yggdrasil）上（Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. "
"30）。该星座的形态及其在银河中的位置均与此模型相符，且这只鹰在秋季的傍晚便可见，这赋予了赫拉斯维尔格作为秋季风暴征兆的角色。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Boiling Well
msgid ""
"Hvergelmir (the boiling well) is one of the springs under Yggdrasil’s three "
"roots. Nidhögg also dwells there, gnawing at the root (Sturluson 2017 [#8], "
"p. 28). The wells are represented by gaps in the bright band of the Milky "
"Way, with a larger dark area near Alhena corresponding to the serpent’s "
"proximity."
msgstr ""
"赫瓦格密尔泉（Hvergelmir，意为沸腾泉）是世界树（Yggdrasil）三条树根之下的泉眼之一。毒蛇尼德霍格（Nidhögg）也栖居于此，啃噬着树根（Sturluson"
" 2017 [#8], p. 28）。这些泉眼以银河明亮光带中的暗隙来表现，其中在井宿三（Alhena）附近的一大片暗区，正对应着巨蛇所处的位置。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Mimir's Well
msgid ""
"Mímis brunnr (Mímir’s well) is the source of wisdom, from which Odin "
"sacrificed his eye to drink (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 28). The wells are "
"depicted by gaps in the bright band of the Milky Way, with the dark area "
"near Vega serving as Mímir’s well, and Vega representing Odin’s sacrificed "
"eye."
msgstr ""
"密密尔泉（Mímis brunnr）是智慧之源，奥丁（Odin）曾在此献出一只眼睛以饮泉水（Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. "
"28）。这些泉眼以银河明亮光带中的暗隙来表现，织女星（Vega）附近的暗区代表密密尔泉，而织女星则象征着奥丁献出的眼睛。"

#. Description of Norse (Edda) constellation Well of Urd
msgid ""
"Urðarbrunnr (well of Urðr) is the spring at which the Æsir hold daily "
"council. To reach it, they ride across Bifröst (Sturluson 2017 [#8], p. 28)."
" The wells are again represented by gaps in the Milky Way, with a larger "
"dark spot at the end of Bifröst near Daneb representing the spring beneath "
"Yggdrasil’s root."
msgstr ""
"乌尔德泉（Urðarbrunnr）是诸神（Æsir）每日举行会议的泉水所在地。为抵达此处，他们需骑马跨越彩虹桥（Bifröst）（Sturluson "
"2017 [#8], p. "
"28）。这些泉眼再次以银河中的暗隙来表现，其中位于彩虹桥末端、天津四（Daneb）附近的一个较大暗斑，代表着位于世界树（Yggdrasil）根部的这处泉眼。"

#. Norse (Edda) sky culture references section in markdown format
msgid ""
" - [#1]: Beckman, N. & Kålund, K. (eds.) (1914–1916) Alfræði íslenzk II: Rímtöl. Copenhagen: Hið íslenzka bókmenntafélag.\n"
" - [#2]: Holmberg, P. (2022) ‘Watching Star Wars with Viking Age Subtitles: An analysis of cohesion and coherence in the Rök runestone inscription’, Arkiv för nordisk filologi, 137, pp. 231–246. (Publication date: 2 May 2025).\n"
" - [#3]: Jonsson, B. (1994) Star Myths of the Vikings: A New Concept of Norse Mythology. Swan River, Manitoba: The Author.\n"
" - [#4]: Krause, A. (2010) Reclam’s Lexicon of Germanic Mythology and Heroic Legend. Stuttgart: Philipp Reclam jun.\n"
" - [#5]: Lorenz, G. (1984) Gylfaginning. Text, translation and commentary. Darmstadt: Wissenschaftliche Buchgesellschaft. (Texte zur Forschung, 48).\n"
" - [#6]: Persson, J.R. (2017) Norse Constellations. ResearchGate. DOI: 10.13140/RG.2.2.15662.92483.\n"
" - [#7]: Sigurðsson, G. (2022) ‘How Gylfi’s Illusion Breathes Life into the Sky’, Religionsvidenskabeligt Tidsskrift, 74, pp. 231–246. DOI: 10.7146/rt.v74i.132105.\n"
" - [#8]: Sturluson, S. (2017) The Edda of Snorri Sturluson. Translated by K. Simrock. Bibliographically updated edition. Stuttgart: Reclam."
msgstr ""

#. Norse (Edda) sky culture authors section in markdown format
msgid ""
"This sky culture was contributed to Stellarium by Jakob Eyermann consulting with Susanne M. Hoffmann as part of a German studies term paper.\n"
"\n"
"### About\n"
"\n"
"Sophie Marshall and Susanne M. Hoffmann served as mentors during the research process. Several constellations were taken from the Rimtöl gloss and thus from Jonas Persson's sky culture “Norse”."
msgstr ""
"此星空文化由雅各布·艾尔曼 (Jakob Eyermann) 咨询苏珊娜·M·霍夫曼 (Susanne M. Hoffmann) 后，作为一项日耳曼研究学期论文的组成部分，贡献至 Stellarium 天文软件。\n"
"\n"
"### 关于贡献\n"
"\n"
"在研究过程中，索菲·马歇尔 (Sophie Marshall) 与苏珊娜·M·霍夫曼 (Susanne M. Hoffmann) 担任导师。其中若干星座取自《Rimtöl》注释，因而也来源于乔纳斯·佩尔松 (Jonas Persson) 的 “Norse” 星图文化体系。"

#. Northern Andes sky culture name
msgid "Northern Andes"
msgstr "北安第斯"

#. Northern Andes sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The Northern Andes have a complex laboratory that teaches us about the "
"different sciences that humanity has contemplated in its history; starting "
"from observation to the various elements that surround us, with the need to "
"ensure our survival as a species and lineage, the human being learned to "
"understand the signals that the cosmos, plants, animals, the climate and "
"other elements emit constantly. Then the wise learned to warn about the "
"changes that affect living beings."
msgstr ""
"北安第斯山脉有一个复杂的实验室，它教我们人类在其历史上所考虑的不同科学； "
"从观察到我们周围的各种元素，为了确保我们作为一个物种和谱系的生存，人类学会了理解宇宙、植物、动物、气候和其他元素不断发出的信号。 "
"智者学会了对影响生命的变化发出警告。"

#. Northern Andes sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"In order to replicate the ancestral measurements in the Andean observatories, we propose the use of a wide-mouth container; in the open we will place it and level properly. In order to create a star mirror we will fill it with water, in this reflection of the sky, the Andean sage can admire and record the movements of the sun, the moon, planets or the stars.\n"
"\n"
"The Stellarium simulator allows us to recreate these \"cosmic mirrors\" and analyze the specific stellar dynamics that are seen in the Northern Andes as well as the millenarian wise men in their patient observation through the ages. These beings have registered the cosmic movements in the current prehispanic heritage of the Andean peoples and produced graphic configurations, which after much joint work by several researchers in several generations at the beginning of the 21st century have been partially decoded.\n"
"\n"
"Here we tell what we found in the equatorial skies:\n"
"\n"
"### The Sun (Punchao o Wilca)\n"
"\n"
"When we find ourselves in the center of the planet, the apparent movement that the sun makes through our annual journey around it is equidistant and proportional. At the equinoxes the sun will cross the center of the sky, on the solstice of June it will travel its southernmost road (it will go north) and on the solstice of December the northernmost path will be traveled (more to the south). These natural phenomena are the marks of the four main festivals that celebrate a specific part of the agricultural calendar because they are the points of inflection between the climatic seasons.\n"
"\n"
"According to the colonial chronicler Juan de Betanzos \"the Indians knew the leap years\"; thanks to the research of Gustavo Guayasamín, a cyclic movement is identified in a four-year interval in the sun; to observe it, we suggest placing ourselves at the March equinox (approximately the March equinoxes are the 21st day in the Gregorian calendar), at the solar daytime (12:20 in the civil time for the year 2018). We can then move forward in time thanks to the \"Date / Time Window\" from year to year and we will notice that the sun moves, returning to the point where the observation begins in periods of four years, for example: It starts in 2016, moves to the left of the spectator in 2017, continues moving to the left in 2018, also moves in 2019 and in 2020 returns to its initial position; then start the cycle again.\n"
"\n"
"### Clear Constellations, Asterisms and Guidelines in the Andes.\n"
"\n"
"We consider that by means of \"stellar mirrors\" the sages could register the stellar traffic. Through this observation they noticed that during the nightfalls of each equinox and solstice, specific stars appear in the sky, as if they were marking the climatic changes to which we are exposed, so these cosmic signals were recorded in the Andean prehispanic patrimony giving rise to the Andean geometrical forms.\n"
"\n"
"#### March Equinox\n"
"\n"
"**\"Antonio Quinatoa\" Cross:** At dusk the first stars to appear are: Sirius - Procyon - Rigel - Betelgeuse, who form the cross named \"Antonio Quinatoa\". It is the constellation that governs the masculine cycle.\n"
"\n"
"#### September Equinox\n"
"\n"
"**Molestina Triangle:** The first stars to appear are: Altair - Vega - Antares who make up the triangle named \"Molestina\"\n"
"\n"
"**Constellation Daniela Alejandra Ayala:** Thanks to the hard work in the registration of the designs, we have identified the clear constellation named \"Daniela Alejandra Ayala\", cosmic set that accompanies the image of the \"Mono Andino\", will appear in the center of the sky at nightfall of the female equinox.\n"
"\n"
"#### June Solstice\n"
"\n"
"**South Cross:** The most outstanding stars in the evening of the Summer Solstice for the Northern Hemisphere are: Acrux, Mimosa, δ Crucis, ζ Crucis, λ Crucis and μ Crucis who form the \"Southern Cross\".\n"
"\n"
"#### December Solstice\n"
"\n"
"**The “Jorge Trujillo” Arrow:** The most outstanding stars in the evening of the winter solstice for the southern hemisphere are Caph - Shedar - Navi - κ Cas, they are part of the western constellation of Cassiopeia, the resulting form evokes the shape of an arrow that at the end of the December solstice It is in an East - West direction.\n"
"\n"
"The asterisms that we include are the first stars to appear at the end of each equinox or solstice. Like the constellations, these basic forms (diamond, square, triangle and arrow), mark the beginning or end of a cycle, apparently human beings discovered and recorded them before the forms in the dark constellations.\n"
"\n"
"### The Sacred Beings in the Cosmos. The Dark Constellations.\n"
"\n"
"#### The Milky Way\n"
"\n"
"Our planet belongs to the galaxy of the Milky Way, whose shape is that of a large disk with two bulging arms; this form and the rotation of the earth means that at the evenings of the equinoxes and solstices we can appreciate a specific part of it, thus becoming a signal that the ancestors appreciated to measure the times. Called in the Andes as the \"Muyun\" for many peoples, it represents a gigantic life-giving serpent.\n"
"\n"
"Contrary to the West, the constellations are not made up of bright points or stars; the astral beings are housed in the \"dark spots\" existing in the brilliance of the Milky Way, so at each of the turning points in our annual path around the sun (Solstices and Equinoxes), we will find a guiding constellation in each \"visible end\" of the galaxy. As with lunar or solar movements, the movements of the constellations in the Northern Andes marked the beginning or end of specific eras, agricultural, civil, reproductive or festive. They determined the fate of beings, receiving respect and veneration for those who came for their wisdom; thus developing a religious thought similar to that of the sun or the moon throughout the continent.\n"
"\n"
"Here we describe the constellations decoded to date:\n"
"\n"
"#### Dark Constellations\n"
"\n"
"|Image|Description|\n"
"|-----|-----------|\n"
"|<img src=\"illustrations/jaguar.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" />|Estelina Quinatoa (The Jaguar): Constellation that governs the male cycle, also called \"Wilca\" or \"Otorongo\", indicates the arrival of the crops of tender grains.|\n"
"|<img src=\"illustrations/mono.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" />|Mercedes Cotacachi (The Monkey): Constellation that governs the female cycle, indicates the arrival of rains and the start of agricultural processes.|\n"
"|<img src=\"illustrations/sapo.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" />|Hernán Crespo Toral (The Frog): The \"Hampatu\" is the animal that has several stages, like the Andean thought, it appears on the night of the June solstice and it is related to the contact with the world of the dead.|\n"
"|<img src=\"illustrations/guerrero.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" />|Ana Jaramillo de Velasteguí (The Warrior): Known as \"the Man and the Spear\" or \"The Dancer\", the constellation governs the December solstice.|"
msgstr ""
"为复原安第斯古天文台的观测方法，我们建议使用广口容器：将其置于露天场所并精确调平。通过注水制造\"星象镜\"，安第斯智者便能藉此天穹倒影观测记录日、月、行星及星辰的运行轨迹。\n"
"\n"
"Stellarium模拟软件使我们能够重现这些\"宇宙镜面\"，既可分析北安第斯地区可见的特定星体运行规律，也能再现千百年来先贤们通过耐心观测获得的智慧。这些先民将天体运行规律镌刻在安第斯民族的前哥伦布时期遗产中，形成了独特的图形符号体系。经过21世纪初多代研究者的通力合作，这些密码已得到部分破译。\n"
"\n"
"我们在赤道天区的发现如下：\n"
"\n"
"### 太阳（Punchao或Wilca）\n"
"\n"
"当我们位于地球赤道时，太阳在周年公转中呈现等距对称的视运动。分至点时太阳横越天穹中央，六月冬至日行至最南轨迹（向北移动），十二月冬至日则运行最北路径（向南移动）。这些自然现象是四大节庆的标志，对应农业历法的特定节点，因其恰处于气候季节的转换点。\n"
"\n"
"殖民时期编年史家胡安·德贝坦索斯记载\"印第安人知晓闰年规律\"。根据古斯塔沃·瓜亚萨明的研究，太阳存在以四年为周期的运动：建议在三月春分日（公历约3月21日）正午时分（2018年民用时间12:20）开始观测。借助\"日期/时间窗口\"逐年推进，可发现太阳呈现周期性位移——例如2016年起始点，2017年偏观察者左侧，2018年持续左移，2019年继续位移，至2020年回归初始位置，继而开启新周期。\n"
"\n"
"### 安第斯明星座、星群与指向标\n"
"\n"
"我们认为智者通过\"星象镜\"记录天体运行轨迹。他们发现每个分至点的黄昏时分，总有特定星群显现于天际，如同标记气候变迁的宇宙信号。这些天象被镌刻在安第斯前哥伦布时期遗产中，演化成独特的几何图形体系。\n"
"\n"
"#### 三月春分\n"
"**\"安东尼奥·基纳托亚\"十字星群：** 黄昏初现的恒星包括天狼星-南河三-参宿七-参宿四，构成命名星群。此星座主导男性周期。\n"
"\n"
"#### 九月秋分\n"
"**莫莱斯蒂纳三角形：** 由牛郎星-织女星-心宿二组成的命名星群。\n"
"\n"
"**丹妮拉·亚历杭德拉·阿亚拉星座：** 通过持续的星象图案记录工作，我们辨识出此明亮星座。该宇宙组合伴随\"安第斯神猴\"图像，在秋分夜幕降临时分显现于天穹中央。\n"
"\n"
"#### 六月冬至\n"
"**南十字星群：** 北半球夏至夜最显著的恒星包括十字架α、β、δ、ζ、λ、μ，共同构成南十字造型。\n"
"\n"
"#### 十二月冬至\n"
"**\"豪尔赫·特鲁希略\"箭矢：** 南半球冬至夜突出的王良四-王良一-策-仙后座κ星属于西方仙后座，其连线形成东-西指向的箭矢造型。\n"
"\n"
"我们收录的星群均在分至点黄昏时分最先显现。与星座类似，这些基础形态（菱形、方形、三角形、箭矢）标志着周期始终，人类发现并记录它们的时间似乎早于暗星座。\n"
"\n"
"### 宇宙神圣存在：暗星座体系\n"
"\n"
"#### 银河\n"
"我们所在的银河系呈双旋臂盘状结构，结合地球自转使得在分至点夜晚可观测到特定银河段落。安第斯各族称其为\"穆云\"，视作赋予生命的巨蛇。\n"
"\n"
"与西方传统不同，这里的星座并非由亮星构成，而是存在于银河辉光中的\"暗斑\"。在我们绕日公转的每个转折点（分至点），都能在银河可见端发现指引性星座。这些星座的运行如同日月运动般，标志着农业、民事、生殖或节庆周期的始终。它们决定众生命运，因蕴含智慧而备受尊崇，由此发展出遍布大陆的类日月宗教观念。\n"
"\n"
"目前已破译的暗星座如下：\n"
"\n"
"#### 暗星座图谱\n"
"\n"
"| 图像 | 描述 |\n"
"|------|------|\n"
"| <img src=\"illustrations/jaguar.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" /> | 埃斯特丽娜·基纳托亚（美洲豹）：主导男性周期的星座，亦称\"威尔卡\"或\"水獭\"，预示嫩谷作物丰收期 |\n"
"| <img src=\"illustrations/mono.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" /> | 梅塞德斯·科塔卡奇（神猴）：主导女性周期的星座，预示雨季来临与农事开端 |\n"
"| <img src=\"illustrations/sapo.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" /> | 埃尔南·克雷斯波·托拉尔（青蛙）：\"汉帕图\"是具有多重蜕变阶段的生物，契合安第斯哲学思想，现身于六月冬至夜，关联冥界沟通 |\n"
"| <img src=\"illustrations/guerrero.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"107\" /> | 安娜·哈拉米略·德贝拉斯特吉（战士）：以\"持矛人\"或\"舞者\"闻名，主宰十二月冬至节令 |"

#. Northern Andes sky culture authors section in markdown format
msgid ""
"These constellations, asterisms and measurements are part of **the legacy of Ancestral Knowledge** protected and compiled by the **Clan Quinatoa, guardians of the millenary knowledge of the Lundauco Valley in Imbabura - Ecuador**\n"
".\n"
"The astral information is based on the study of Andrés Alejandro Ayala Quinatoa in \"Millenary Astronomy, what my teachers and ancestors taught me\"; Servio Jr. Paladines collaborates for the computer integration.\n"
"\n"
"The present illustrations are inspired by the pre-Hispanic designs of the Pasto nation investigated by Estelina Quinatoa for the book \"Ancestral Representations and Colors of the Cosmos\" (Ministry of Culture and Heritage of Ecuador)."
msgstr ""
"这些星座、星群与观测方法构成了**祖传智慧遗产**的重要组成部分，由**厄瓜多尔因巴布拉省伦道科河谷千年智慧守护者——基纳托亚家族**保护并整理。\n"
"\n"
"星象资料基于安德烈斯·亚历杭德罗·阿亚拉·基纳托亚著作《千年天文学——师长与祖先传授我的智慧》的研究成果，塞维奥·帕拉迪内斯负责计算机技术整合。\n"
"\n"
"本图录创作灵感源自埃斯特丽娜·基纳托亚为《宇宙的祖源表征与色彩》（厄瓜多尔文化传承部出版）一书研究的帕斯托民族前西班牙时期传统纹样。"

#. Romanian sky culture name
msgid "Romanian"
msgstr "罗马尼亚"

#. Romanian sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"Considered as a whole, Romanian popular stellar mythology has three "
"essential components."
msgstr ""

#. Romanian sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The FIRST one - the ancestral pastoral-agricultural is pre-Christian, in which the sky seen both as an agrarian clock for specific activities and as an \"exhibition\" of agricultural tools used by peasants.\n"
"\n"
"The SECOND component - more recent - corresponding to the Christianization of Romanian geographical space and repositioning in the sky the Christian and pre-Christian elements where constellations are associated with cosmogonical and theogonical myths, so that the sky is seen more like a church.\n"
"\n"
"And the THIRD component - the origin of the Romanian people, projecting on the sky the synthesis of formation of this people (the conquest of Dacia by the Romans) through projection of dramatic scenes from this history of Dacians mixing with the Romans.\n"
"\n"
"**Note**: in Western Constellation Orion there are four Traditional Romanian Constellations that are overlapping."
msgstr ""

